1
00:00:06,047 --> 00:00:08,550
Let's take some time
to get to know each other.

2
00:00:08,633 --> 00:00:10,593
- Introductions?
- Yeah, introductions.

3
00:00:10,677 --> 00:00:13,596
I'm most curious about Chae-won
and Chae-eun's father.

4
00:00:13,680 --> 00:00:17,142
- You're curious about me?
- You went for a run this morning, right?

5
00:00:17,976 --> 00:00:21,730
He, uh…
His work involves running, in a way.

6
00:00:21,813 --> 00:00:23,398
What kind of job has you running around?

7
00:00:23,481 --> 00:00:25,150
Is working out is his job?

8
00:00:25,900 --> 00:00:28,862
When you came in,
I noticed you had a duffel bag.

9
00:00:28,945 --> 00:00:31,906
- Like some kind of like army backpack.
- Yeah, it's kind of military-style.

10
00:00:31,990 --> 00:00:34,284
I thought maybe you worked
in the military.

11
00:00:34,367 --> 00:00:35,827
Is he a soldier?

12
00:00:35,910 --> 00:00:38,329
IS HE ACTUALLY A SOLDIER?

13
00:00:38,413 --> 00:00:40,957
- I'll come out and say it.
- Ah, yes, yes.

14
00:00:41,041 --> 00:00:45,045
I did work as a soldier
in the 707th Special Mission Group.

15
00:00:45,128 --> 00:00:46,171
Yes, yes.

16
00:00:46,254 --> 00:00:50,508
I serve as the last line of defense
for our citizens' safety,

17
00:00:50,592 --> 00:00:52,844
the Seoul Police Special Operations Unit.

18
00:00:54,929 --> 00:00:56,639
POLICE SPECIAL OPERATIONS UNIT:

19
00:00:56,723 --> 00:00:58,850
RESPONDS TO VIOLENT CRIMES
AND TERROR ATTACKS

20
00:00:58,933 --> 00:01:01,478
AND PROVIDES SECURITY SUPPORT
FOR MAJOR NATIONAL EVENTS

21
00:01:01,561 --> 00:01:02,937
For real?

22
00:01:05,106 --> 00:01:06,691
- That's so cool.
- Amazing.

23
00:01:06,775 --> 00:01:08,401
That's sick.

24
00:01:08,485 --> 00:01:10,070
Oh, my goodness.

25
00:01:10,904 --> 00:01:11,988
Well, that's…

26
00:01:12,072 --> 00:01:16,201
- Oh, I… I've been so disrespectful.
- That's so cool.

27
00:01:16,284 --> 00:01:17,786
So disrespectful.

28
00:01:17,869 --> 00:01:19,621
Oh, yes!

29
00:01:19,704 --> 00:01:22,207
Careful, dude. You're making us seem old.

30
00:01:22,290 --> 00:01:25,460
His jokes aren't funny,
but he really tries, huh?

31
00:01:25,543 --> 00:01:28,171
- Is he always like this?
- Yeah, he likes to joke.

32
00:01:28,254 --> 00:01:30,006
I'm sorry.

33
00:01:30,090 --> 00:01:32,175
I mean, you didn't know before,

34
00:01:32,258 --> 00:01:34,803
but now that you hear it,
it's a twist, isn't it?

35
00:01:34,886 --> 00:01:37,847
This is so weird.
You look more handsome now.

36
00:01:38,890 --> 00:01:40,683
- Exactly.
- He looks different now

37
00:01:40,767 --> 00:01:42,602
that I know he's in
the Special Operations Unit.

38
00:01:42,685 --> 00:01:45,480
I may seem gentle on the outside,
but I've got toughness in me.

39
00:01:45,563 --> 00:01:46,564
I protect people.

40
00:01:46,648 --> 00:01:48,358
- Incredible.
- How cool. Wow.

41
00:01:48,441 --> 00:01:49,442
Nice.

42
00:01:49,526 --> 00:01:51,986
- Amazing.
- Pretty cool, huh?

43
00:01:52,070 --> 00:01:53,738
You know, it's no wonder.

44
00:01:53,822 --> 00:01:56,449
His two daughters weren't
embarrassed by him,

45
00:01:56,533 --> 00:01:58,368
no matter what he was doing, right?

46
00:01:58,451 --> 00:02:00,120
- Yeah, you're right.
- Yeah.

47
00:02:00,203 --> 00:02:02,413
- Let me introduce myself now.
- Go on.

48
00:02:02,497 --> 00:02:05,375
- I'm a senior, and the CSAT is in a week.
- Wow.

49
00:02:05,458 --> 00:02:07,210
- What?
- No way.

50
00:02:07,293 --> 00:02:09,921
- You're a high school senior?
- Wait, Chae-eun.

51
00:02:10,004 --> 00:02:11,965
What are you doing?

52
00:02:12,048 --> 00:02:14,259
- You shouldn't be here right now.
- That's crazy.

53
00:02:14,342 --> 00:02:17,387
- The CSAT is next week.
- Oh, that's true. It's next week.

54
00:02:17,470 --> 00:02:19,472
- It's only a week away?
- It's next week.

55
00:02:19,556 --> 00:02:22,433
You're not supposed to be here,
making toast!

56
00:02:22,517 --> 00:02:25,979
For us, being on <i>Jae-seok's B&B Rules!</i>
is way more important.

57
00:02:26,062 --> 00:02:28,940
We're having a better experience here,
so we're happy.

58
00:02:29,023 --> 00:02:31,568
As a parent myself,
I don't know what I'd do

59
00:02:31,651 --> 00:02:34,112
- with the CSAT just a week away.
- Right, that's amazing.

60
00:02:34,195 --> 00:02:36,531
I wonder if I'd be able to make
the same choice.

61
00:02:36,614 --> 00:02:38,658
Aw, he's such a good dad.

62
00:02:38,741 --> 00:02:41,452
But still, you're ready for the CSAT,
right?

63
00:02:41,536 --> 00:02:44,956
I want to be a police officer, so I'm
focusing on the civil service exam.

64
00:02:45,039 --> 00:02:47,458
- Ah.
- Ah. Really?

65
00:02:47,542 --> 00:02:50,170
I think that's why I respect him
even more. He has my dream job.

66
00:02:50,253 --> 00:02:52,505
It's great that you respect your dad.

67
00:02:52,589 --> 00:02:55,633
So, yeah,
my dad's basically my role model.

68
00:02:56,801 --> 00:02:59,596
- To be a dad and hear that must be…
- He must love it, yeah.

69
00:02:59,679 --> 00:03:01,347
- He must be so happy.
- That's so sweet.

70
00:03:01,431 --> 00:03:03,975
Wow, Kwang-chul. Wow.

71
00:03:04,058 --> 00:03:05,852
I feel like I'm going to cry.

72
00:03:05,935 --> 00:03:07,729
Oh, look! He's actually tearing up.

73
00:03:07,812 --> 00:03:09,272
Whoa.

74
00:03:09,355 --> 00:03:11,316
So cool that her dream is to be
like her dad.

75
00:03:11,399 --> 00:03:12,400
Yeah, that's great.

76
00:03:12,483 --> 00:03:14,402
Is that the first time she said that?

77
00:03:14,485 --> 00:03:17,280
She says it all the time,
but I always tear up.

78
00:03:19,782 --> 00:03:21,534
I'm an F-type. I'm sorry.

79
00:03:22,160 --> 00:03:25,413
- I get it, though. Yeah, totally.
- Yeah, I get it.

80
00:03:26,289 --> 00:03:28,333
- Oh, no, Chae-eun!
- She's crying too.

81
00:03:28,416 --> 00:03:30,960
She's an F too.

82
00:03:33,463 --> 00:03:35,757
Being a police officer is a dangerous job,

83
00:03:35,840 --> 00:03:37,717
so at first I didn't consider it.

84
00:03:37,800 --> 00:03:40,845
But watching my dad,
I started wanting to become one too.

85
00:03:40,929 --> 00:03:43,348
As a dad, and as a daughter,

86
00:03:43,431 --> 00:03:46,434
you must both just be so proud
of one another, right?

87
00:03:47,435 --> 00:03:48,728
You really must be.

88
00:03:50,271 --> 00:03:52,815
Gosh, it got me a little emotional too.

89
00:03:52,899 --> 00:03:54,817
My parents divorced when I was young,

90
00:03:54,901 --> 00:03:57,528
and I grew up without much
of a father figure.

91
00:03:57,612 --> 00:03:59,155
So to be honest,

92
00:03:59,239 --> 00:04:02,617
I guess I've always had a somewhat
negative view of marriage.

93
00:04:02,700 --> 00:04:05,245
But watching his family, I thought,

94
00:04:05,328 --> 00:04:07,372
"Maybe I really could become
a good father too.

95
00:04:07,455 --> 00:04:09,374
I could follow his example
and be like that."

96
00:04:10,375 --> 00:04:12,794
- That's so nice to see.
- Yeah, it is.

97
00:04:12,877 --> 00:04:16,631
He's always goofing around
with his daughters like they're friends,

98
00:04:16,714 --> 00:04:20,510
but through it all, they still seem
to respect him so much.

99
00:04:21,719 --> 00:04:24,722
Getting to see their beautiful
relationship here at the B&B

100
00:04:24,806 --> 00:04:26,891
has felt like such a gift for us.

101
00:04:26,975 --> 00:04:28,768
Here, dry your eyes.

102
00:04:30,478 --> 00:04:33,189
Whoa, crying from both sides.
That must be tough.

103
00:04:34,107 --> 00:04:36,234
That must be tough.

104
00:04:36,317 --> 00:04:38,987
You could at least pretend!

105
00:04:40,113 --> 00:04:43,700
Uh, Chae-won. Could you
introduce yourself as well, please?

106
00:04:43,783 --> 00:04:46,619
I'm… in middle school.

107
00:04:46,703 --> 00:04:47,704
- Adorable.
- Ah, I knew it.

108
00:04:47,787 --> 00:04:49,789
- Eighth grade.
- Oh, she's in middle school?

109
00:04:49,872 --> 00:04:52,000
Is that it? Nothing else?

110
00:04:52,083 --> 00:04:55,211
LET'S GIVE IT UP FOR CHAE-WON,
A SECOND-YEAR MIDDLE SCHOOLER

111
00:04:55,295 --> 00:04:57,630
- Those are the worst two years.
- Rebel years.

112
00:04:57,714 --> 00:05:00,133
Chae-won seems like
a really good kid to me.

113
00:05:00,216 --> 00:05:02,468
- She didn't rebel.
- Right.

114
00:05:02,552 --> 00:05:06,514
Chae-won, you've been here with us
for a day. How has it been?

115
00:05:06,597 --> 00:05:08,850
First of all, I get to miss school.

116
00:05:08,933 --> 00:05:11,185
That's the best part for sure.

117
00:05:11,269 --> 00:05:12,937
I'm really happy to be here.

118
00:05:13,896 --> 00:05:16,316
Moving on, we've got a trio.
Young-gwang and two others.

119
00:05:16,399 --> 00:05:18,776
- I know a bit about them.
- I'm really curious. Yeah.

120
00:05:18,860 --> 00:05:20,611
Yeah, I'm so curious.

121
00:05:20,695 --> 00:05:23,323
Their job has them working
5:00 a.m. to 9:00 p.m.

122
00:05:23,406 --> 00:05:24,407
What?

123
00:05:24,490 --> 00:05:26,868
Well, we start work at 6:00,
but we get up at 5:00.

124
00:05:26,951 --> 00:05:29,203
We work long hours, we work weekends,

125
00:05:29,287 --> 00:05:32,915
and we really aren't allowed to
take time off whenever we want.

126
00:05:32,999 --> 00:05:36,085
That's why he said at the beginning
that he didn't wanna do anything!

127
00:05:38,129 --> 00:05:41,424
He's the one who was standing alone
in the field in his parka!

128
00:05:41,507 --> 00:05:44,886
Let's do a survey
about your stay here at the B&B.

129
00:05:44,969 --> 00:05:49,140
"I want to try one of those quizzes
or games I've only seen on TV."

130
00:05:49,223 --> 00:05:51,392
- I'd love to try them.
- I wanna try.

131
00:05:51,476 --> 00:05:52,977
Oh, you say no?

132
00:05:53,603 --> 00:05:54,645
- You say no?
- Yeah.

133
00:05:54,729 --> 00:05:57,523
- You don't care about trying them?
- What do you wanna do?

134
00:05:58,399 --> 00:06:00,193
I was a little surprised.

135
00:06:00,276 --> 00:06:02,695
Most people are all excited
when they come here

136
00:06:02,779 --> 00:06:04,447
and want to try different things.

137
00:06:04,530 --> 00:06:07,283
But I've never met anyone
like Mr. Lee-joong.

138
00:06:08,534 --> 00:06:10,578
We told him that he might as well
just go home.

139
00:06:10,661 --> 00:06:12,330
- Lee-joong, that was you?
- Yeah, that's right.

140
00:06:12,413 --> 00:06:14,749
- We'll try to guess.
- Yeah, sure.

141
00:06:14,832 --> 00:06:16,584
First, firefighter.

142
00:06:16,667 --> 00:06:17,668
That's not it.

143
00:06:17,752 --> 00:06:20,213
You could run into the three of us
at any time.

144
00:06:20,296 --> 00:06:22,382
We could run into you at any time?

145
00:06:23,299 --> 00:06:24,467
This is so hard.

146
00:06:24,550 --> 00:06:25,968
Police dispatcher.

147
00:06:26,052 --> 00:06:27,887
- Paramedic!
- Not that.

148
00:06:28,638 --> 00:06:30,515
- Funeral director?
- Huh?

149
00:06:30,598 --> 00:06:33,559
He said we could run into them anytime,
so I was like, eventually?

150
00:06:33,643 --> 00:06:35,103
I just meant there's a chance.

151
00:06:35,186 --> 00:06:38,231
Actually, if you ever see us,
it wouldn't be for a good reason.

152
00:06:38,314 --> 00:06:39,732
Wow, this is too hard.

153
00:06:41,109 --> 00:06:42,652
Prison guard. Prison guard.

154
00:06:42,735 --> 00:06:44,362
- Prison guard?
- Prison guard.

155
00:06:44,445 --> 00:06:45,613
- Correct.
- You got it.

156
00:06:45,696 --> 00:06:47,156
- I was right?
- She was right?

157
00:06:48,282 --> 00:06:49,700
Prison guard?

158
00:06:49,784 --> 00:06:51,744
- Wow!
- Wow!

159
00:06:51,828 --> 00:06:53,830
- Prison… Oh.
- Oh, that's why…

160
00:06:53,913 --> 00:06:56,791
- You're prison guards.
- We work at Anyang Correctional.

161
00:06:56,874 --> 00:06:58,167
Anyang Correctional?

162
00:06:58,251 --> 00:07:00,420
We're on the Rapid Patrol Team.

163
00:07:00,503 --> 00:07:03,005
- We suppress riots and things like that.
- Suppress riots?

164
00:07:03,089 --> 00:07:04,715
- Yeah.
- Wow.

165
00:07:04,799 --> 00:07:07,093
But why are your shifts so long?

166
00:07:07,176 --> 00:07:09,470
We're on the clock from the early morning,

167
00:07:09,554 --> 00:07:11,973
when the inmates wake up,
until they go to bed.

168
00:07:12,056 --> 00:07:14,183
So that's why you didn't wanna
do anything.

169
00:07:14,267 --> 00:07:17,103
- Oh, yes.
- Oh, I see. I get it now.

170
00:07:17,186 --> 00:07:21,524
It said we could come here, relax,
and have some fun, but it's…

171
00:07:21,607 --> 00:07:23,359
- Yeah?
- …busier than I expected.

172
00:07:24,944 --> 00:07:27,238
REASON FOR APPLYING:
TO GET SOME REST

173
00:07:27,321 --> 00:07:29,282
But we're usually stuck
in a confined place,

174
00:07:29,365 --> 00:07:31,492
so getting out like this
feels really great.

175
00:07:31,576 --> 00:07:33,578
- Oh, so you like it here?
- Yeah.

176
00:07:33,661 --> 00:07:35,872
All right, let's move on to this side.

177
00:07:35,955 --> 00:07:39,333
- I really wanna know about Bryan too.
- Seriously.

178
00:07:39,417 --> 00:07:41,919
He kept saying
he was protecting the earth.

179
00:07:42,003 --> 00:07:45,131
It's nothing, really.
I merely protect the earth for my job.

180
00:07:45,840 --> 00:07:48,676
- He said he was protecting the earth?
- Yeah, he said he protected the earth.

181
00:07:48,759 --> 00:07:51,012
Ah, some kind of mystery man.

182
00:07:51,095 --> 00:07:54,724
First of all, I don't protect the earth.
I was just joking.

183
00:07:54,807 --> 00:07:56,100
You lied?

184
00:07:56,893 --> 00:07:59,520
I'm do taekwondo for Kyung Hee University.

185
00:08:01,564 --> 00:08:03,649
Oh, you do taekwondo.

186
00:08:03,733 --> 00:08:06,402
I also made the World Taekwondo
Demonstration Team.

187
00:08:06,486 --> 00:08:09,405
We travel around the world,
performing for audiences.

188
00:08:10,531 --> 00:08:12,700
How long have you have you been doing it?

189
00:08:12,783 --> 00:08:15,328
I started in the first grade,
and I've been doing it ever since.

190
00:08:15,411 --> 00:08:18,206
But he said his nationality wasn't Korean.

191
00:08:18,289 --> 00:08:19,790
You're from Korea, right?

192
00:08:19,874 --> 00:08:22,418
No, I'm from the Democratic Republic
of the Congo.

193
00:08:23,669 --> 00:08:26,631
Oh, so you're a taekwondo martial artist.

194
00:08:26,714 --> 00:08:29,842
- Sang-soon used to do taekwondo too.
- Stop.

195
00:08:29,926 --> 00:08:31,511
- Sang-soon used to--
- Stop it.

196
00:08:32,220 --> 00:08:34,847
All right, then. Now, Seung-jun.

197
00:08:34,931 --> 00:08:37,350
- We kind of know what Seung-jun does.
- We've got a rough idea.

198
00:08:37,433 --> 00:08:38,643
We've got a rough idea.

199
00:08:38,726 --> 00:08:41,437
- Oh, a metal band?
- Yeah. He's in a band.

200
00:08:41,521 --> 00:08:43,606
I think that's the only way
to truly conquer the world.

201
00:08:43,689 --> 00:08:45,942
- I'd say you're in your mid-30s.
- Seriously?

202
00:08:46,025 --> 00:08:48,569
You also look like
you could be in your 20s.

203
00:08:48,653 --> 00:08:50,530
- Oh, yeah?
- I keep going back and forth.

204
00:08:50,613 --> 00:08:53,741
- Funny. He keeps going back and forth.
- Oh!

205
00:08:53,824 --> 00:08:55,618
I'm actually 20.

206
00:08:55,701 --> 00:08:57,036
- Twenty?
- You're 20?

207
00:08:57,119 --> 00:08:58,663
What?

208
00:08:58,746 --> 00:09:00,081
Don't lie to us.

209
00:09:00,164 --> 00:09:02,583
- We thought you might be in your mid-30s.
- Yeah.

210
00:09:02,667 --> 00:09:04,460
I think it's your hair.

211
00:09:05,461 --> 00:09:07,421
I'm in my sophomore year
at KAIST right now.

212
00:09:07,505 --> 00:09:09,048
KAIST?

213
00:09:11,008 --> 00:09:13,719
He's 20, so he started at 18.

214
00:09:13,803 --> 00:09:15,471
Hold on, when did you enter KAIST?

215
00:09:15,555 --> 00:09:17,974
I graduated high school a year early

216
00:09:18,057 --> 00:09:20,309
and then was accepted
through early admission.

217
00:09:20,393 --> 00:09:22,061
He must be a genius.

218
00:09:22,937 --> 00:09:24,897
I'm starting my military service
next year,

219
00:09:24,981 --> 00:09:27,984
so I wanted to gain as much experience
as I could before I go.

220
00:09:28,067 --> 00:09:29,735
I thought that'd help me
with my career path.

221
00:09:29,819 --> 00:09:31,654
Was he always this well spoken?

222
00:09:31,737 --> 00:09:34,991
He's even talking differently now. I'm
kind of shocked. It feels like a movie.

223
00:09:35,074 --> 00:09:37,785
Now that we know he goes to KAIST,
it kind of feels…

224
00:09:37,868 --> 00:09:41,497
Honestly, I definitely thought, "He needs
the army" during our conversations.

225
00:09:41,581 --> 00:09:42,790
To be honest.

226
00:09:43,791 --> 00:09:46,794
But in the future, you never know.

227
00:09:46,877 --> 00:09:49,463
- He might be on the news someday.
- Right, that's right.

228
00:09:49,547 --> 00:09:50,923
All right, now…

229
00:09:51,007 --> 00:09:52,300
LAUGHING

230
00:09:52,383 --> 00:09:53,384
(IS IT OUR TURN?)

231
00:09:53,467 --> 00:09:56,304
- I thought you'd forgotten us.
- How could I forget you? Min-ju.

232
00:09:56,387 --> 00:09:57,388
I mean, me?

233
00:09:57,471 --> 00:09:59,557
You might forget me,
but I won't forget you.

234
00:09:59,640 --> 00:10:03,519
All right, the four of you. Could you
tell us a little bit about yourselves?

235
00:10:03,603 --> 00:10:07,148
Well, as you all know,
I'm Park Hye-jeong, a weight lifter.

236
00:10:07,231 --> 00:10:08,441
I'm 23 years old.

237
00:10:08,524 --> 00:10:11,319
Well, I was really surprised.
I never expected…

238
00:10:11,402 --> 00:10:12,820
I was like, "Who's that?"

239
00:10:12,903 --> 00:10:14,113
It was Hye-jeong.

240
00:10:14,196 --> 00:10:16,866
So the three of them
are your teammates? Is that right?

241
00:10:16,949 --> 00:10:18,409
ARE THE OTHER THREE
WEIGHT LIFTERS TOO?

242
00:10:18,492 --> 00:10:19,493
Tell us. Yeah.

243
00:10:19,577 --> 00:10:21,621
I'm a weight lifter as well.

244
00:10:23,372 --> 00:10:26,876
I'm also a weight lifter on the same team.
I'm 22 years old.

245
00:10:26,959 --> 00:10:30,171
I'm a weight lifter
at Korea National Sport University.

246
00:10:33,466 --> 00:10:35,092
- They're all weight lifters.
- Weight lifters.

247
00:10:35,176 --> 00:10:37,553
As a weight lifter, how much can you lift?

248
00:10:37,637 --> 00:10:42,767
I can snatch 131 kilograms
and clean-and-jerk 171 kilograms.

249
00:10:42,850 --> 00:10:44,185
171?

250
00:10:44,268 --> 00:10:46,270
So you can all lift 100 kilos?

251
00:10:47,730 --> 00:10:50,024
Wow, that's amazing. You're all so petite.

252
00:10:50,107 --> 00:10:51,400
Wow. But they're so small.

253
00:10:51,484 --> 00:10:53,402
I have been training
since I was a student,

254
00:10:53,486 --> 00:10:55,821
so I haven't really had much experience

255
00:10:55,905 --> 00:10:58,783
with retreats or field trips or anything.

256
00:10:58,866 --> 00:11:00,326
That's why I came here.

257
00:11:00,409 --> 00:11:02,244
How's it been for you, Min-ju?

258
00:11:02,328 --> 00:11:04,038
Oh, I'm loving it.

259
00:11:05,289 --> 00:11:06,332
I'm loving it.

260
00:11:08,959 --> 00:11:11,462
You know, you keep looking
at Woo-seok like…

261
00:11:15,716 --> 00:11:17,468
Hold up. What are you doing, Woo-seok?

262
00:11:17,551 --> 00:11:19,887
But, Hye-jeong, you asked us
to film reels with you.

263
00:11:19,970 --> 00:11:22,765
I know. That's what's so annoying!

264
00:11:22,848 --> 00:11:24,934
Wherever they are, their eyes are always…

265
00:11:25,017 --> 00:11:26,602
THEIR EYES ARE ALWAYS
ON WOO-SEOK

266
00:11:26,686 --> 00:11:28,854
You'll all have fish eyes at this rate.

267
00:11:28,938 --> 00:11:31,148
Would you say your job
is especially tough?

268
00:11:31,232 --> 00:11:33,693
Well, my injury's been hurting
quite a bit.

269
00:11:33,776 --> 00:11:34,860
- Oh, your body hurts?
- Yes.

270
00:11:34,944 --> 00:11:36,320
Don't get hurt.

271
00:11:36,404 --> 00:11:37,571
Ugh, here we go.

272
00:11:38,155 --> 00:11:39,949
Aw, we won't.

273
00:11:41,367 --> 00:11:44,954
Yeah, the four of you seem to be
having the time of your lives.

274
00:11:45,037 --> 00:11:46,455
INDISPUTABLE

275
00:11:46,539 --> 00:11:47,998
It's so annoying!

276
00:11:48,082 --> 00:11:50,543
It's not like there's anything
that special going on,

277
00:11:50,626 --> 00:11:52,920
but they're just blissed-out over there.

278
00:11:53,003 --> 00:11:54,880
I find it so annoying.

279
00:11:54,964 --> 00:11:58,217
Anyway, moving on to the two brothers,
Nam-jin and Nam-soon.

280
00:11:58,300 --> 00:12:02,346
Our father was in charge
of a hardware store for a long time

281
00:12:02,430 --> 00:12:04,682
and basically raised us on that income.

282
00:12:04,765 --> 00:12:06,976
And then, about ten years ago,

283
00:12:07,059 --> 00:12:09,687
the two of us took over the store,
and we've been running it since.

284
00:12:09,770 --> 00:12:11,105
- Wow, so quite a while.
- Yeah.

285
00:12:11,188 --> 00:12:12,732
- Is this real?
- Huh?

286
00:12:13,733 --> 00:12:15,067
No, I think it's poly.

287
00:12:15,151 --> 00:12:16,777
The stones look like sponges.

288
00:12:16,861 --> 00:12:18,863
They look like Styrofoam.

289
00:12:18,946 --> 00:12:21,615
I've got to say,
I'm worried about the store.

290
00:12:21,699 --> 00:12:24,285
- Oh, that's cool. Yeah.
- Wow.

291
00:12:24,368 --> 00:12:27,955
I'm sure it's not an easy thing
for brothers to come here together.

292
00:12:28,038 --> 00:12:29,498
- It's not common.
- Yeah.

293
00:12:29,582 --> 00:12:31,959
You said we seem really close,

294
00:12:32,042 --> 00:12:35,963
but there was something
that brought us way closer,

295
00:12:36,046 --> 00:12:38,132
and our bond has only grown since then.

296
00:12:38,215 --> 00:12:41,093
My brother went through
a really tough time,

297
00:12:41,177 --> 00:12:44,638
and I had this crazy idea that
maybe we could come here

298
00:12:44,722 --> 00:12:47,183
and make some really
meaningful memories together.

299
00:12:47,266 --> 00:12:48,559
Sorry.

300
00:12:48,642 --> 00:12:50,102
- It's okay.
- Yeah.

301
00:12:50,186 --> 00:12:52,271
- So I applied for it.
- You did good.

302
00:12:55,274 --> 00:12:56,817
Aw, that's really…

303
00:12:56,901 --> 00:12:58,694
That's so nice.

304
00:12:58,778 --> 00:13:01,280
Now, Ye-rin,
can I ask what you do for a living?

305
00:13:01,363 --> 00:13:02,907
Oh, work in a bank.

306
00:13:04,450 --> 00:13:06,786
I used to be a kindergarten teacher.

307
00:13:06,869 --> 00:13:08,412
- That suits you so well.
- I know.

308
00:13:08,496 --> 00:13:10,539
- It totally suits you.
- Right.

309
00:13:10,623 --> 00:13:14,168
Back in high school, it was actually me
who wanted to be a banker.

310
00:13:14,251 --> 00:13:16,212
I'm studying right now to give it a try.

311
00:13:16,295 --> 00:13:18,923
So you're studying to become a banker
right now. To get a job at a bank.

312
00:13:19,006 --> 00:13:22,802
- Oh, so you are friends from high school.
- We've been fiends since high school.

313
00:13:22,885 --> 00:13:24,845
I'm studying law in college.

314
00:13:25,513 --> 00:13:28,432
I'm studying advertising
and public relations in college.

315
00:13:28,516 --> 00:13:29,850
Whoa.

316
00:13:29,934 --> 00:13:31,310
It suits her.

317
00:13:31,393 --> 00:13:33,604
- I have a nickname.
- Let me guess.

318
00:13:33,687 --> 00:13:36,690
Sure, go ahead.
It's kinda like a play on my name.

319
00:13:36,774 --> 00:13:38,150
Yeomyeong?

320
00:13:38,234 --> 00:13:39,985
You mean the hangover cure?

321
00:13:40,820 --> 00:13:42,404
Do you really go to KAIST?

322
00:13:43,113 --> 00:13:46,367
Yeomyeong 808? Yeomyeong 808.

323
00:13:46,450 --> 00:13:48,536
This kid must like to party.

324
00:13:48,619 --> 00:13:51,372
My nickname is actually "Gwiyeowon."

325
00:13:51,455 --> 00:13:53,165
- "Gwiyeowon."
- "Gwiyeowon."

326
00:13:53,249 --> 00:13:54,959
Ah!

327
00:13:55,042 --> 00:13:57,044
- Ah!
- "Gwiyeowon."

328
00:13:57,127 --> 00:13:58,295
- Oh, "Gwiyeowon"!
- Yeah.

329
00:13:58,379 --> 00:14:00,589
And to be honest, I came up with it.

330
00:14:02,007 --> 00:14:03,759
SELF-DUBBED, NOT GIVEN BY OTHERS

331
00:14:03,843 --> 00:14:06,470
It wasn't long, but I really loved

332
00:14:06,554 --> 00:14:09,056
getting to talk with you all like this.

333
00:14:09,139 --> 00:14:11,058
Everyone's so amazing.

334
00:14:11,141 --> 00:14:13,227
- There are so many professions.
- Yeah.

335
00:14:13,310 --> 00:14:16,564
The questions shifted to things like,
"What do you like?"

336
00:14:16,647 --> 00:14:18,065
or "What do you wanna eat?"

337
00:14:18,148 --> 00:14:19,859
There weren't any judgments towards anyone

338
00:14:19,942 --> 00:14:22,987
since we were seeing each other
for who we are, not what we do.

339
00:14:23,070 --> 00:14:25,698
I found everyone really cool
and impressive

340
00:14:25,781 --> 00:14:27,324
once they revealed their jobs.

341
00:14:27,408 --> 00:14:29,535
It's fascinating, isn't it?

342
00:14:30,327 --> 00:14:32,872
Well, I'm sorry to break the bad news,

343
00:14:32,955 --> 00:14:35,666
but Hyo-ri and Sang-soon
have to head out soon.

344
00:14:35,749 --> 00:14:36,917
Such a shame.

345
00:14:37,001 --> 00:14:38,252
- It's a shame.
- Yeah.

346
00:14:38,335 --> 00:14:41,046
With Jae-seok running the B&B,

347
00:14:41,130 --> 00:14:44,842
I got to come as a guest,
and I felt so much more at ease.

348
00:14:44,925 --> 00:14:47,761
I could really take my time
with each person

349
00:14:47,845 --> 00:14:50,264
and have proper conversations,
which I loved.

350
00:14:50,347 --> 00:14:53,559
I hope you all have a great time
with Jae-seok for the rest of your stay.

351
00:14:53,642 --> 00:14:55,519
I'm so grateful that we got to be here.

352
00:14:55,603 --> 00:14:58,397
I think this is such a great opportunity.

353
00:14:58,480 --> 00:15:02,026
I really hope that you all enjoy
every moment while you're here.

354
00:15:02,109 --> 00:15:03,319
Let's give it up for them.

355
00:15:03,402 --> 00:15:04,737
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

356
00:15:07,448 --> 00:15:10,409
You've given me a lot of great advice.

357
00:15:11,368 --> 00:15:13,996
Once you're feeling better,
come volunteer with me sometime.

358
00:15:14,079 --> 00:15:15,664
I will. Thank you.

359
00:15:16,498 --> 00:15:19,376
- Enjoy the rest of your stay.
- Okay, thank you.

360
00:15:19,460 --> 00:15:20,461
Good luck.

361
00:15:20,544 --> 00:15:23,297
- I hope you have fun with your daughters.
- Thank you.

362
00:15:25,466 --> 00:15:26,884
Oh, boy.

363
00:15:26,967 --> 00:15:29,511
We'd better just trying to slip out,
right?

364
00:15:29,595 --> 00:15:32,389
- Yeah, you're right.
- Let's pack up our stuff first.

365
00:15:33,098 --> 00:15:35,935
How nice would it be to love
and respect your parents like that?

366
00:15:36,018 --> 00:15:38,687
- I know, right?
- I envy them so much.

367
00:15:38,771 --> 00:15:41,815
How great would it be
if your daughter said she respects you

368
00:15:41,899 --> 00:15:43,609
and wants to follow in your footsteps?

369
00:15:43,692 --> 00:15:47,780
And the dad isn't overbearing at all.
They're more like friends.

370
00:15:47,863 --> 00:15:50,407
That's because he's so good to them.

371
00:15:50,491 --> 00:15:52,785
We could be like that too, couldn't we?

372
00:15:53,827 --> 00:15:55,079
We'd be like a team.

373
00:15:56,038 --> 00:15:57,164
Teammates.

374
00:16:01,293 --> 00:16:03,462
Let's sneak out while they're talking.

375
00:16:03,963 --> 00:16:05,339
THEY QUIETLY HEAD OUT

376
00:16:05,422 --> 00:16:07,216
The thing is…

377
00:16:07,299 --> 00:16:08,759
Hold on, my shoes.

378
00:16:10,302 --> 00:16:12,221
WIDE OPEN

379
00:16:12,304 --> 00:16:13,806
Oh!

380
00:16:13,889 --> 00:16:14,890
Hyo-ri, are you leaving?

381
00:16:14,974 --> 00:16:16,183
- No.
- Then what?

382
00:16:16,266 --> 00:16:17,726
Just getting ready.

383
00:16:17,810 --> 00:16:20,104
- We're putting our things in the car.
- We're loading it up.

384
00:16:20,187 --> 00:16:22,314
- You have to drive down there, right?
- We do, yeah.

385
00:16:22,398 --> 00:16:23,399
One second.

386
00:16:23,482 --> 00:16:26,276
Ugh, hyung. Thank you, hyung.

387
00:16:27,194 --> 00:16:29,488
- Do you really have to go?
- We should go.

388
00:16:29,571 --> 00:16:31,031
Bye!

389
00:16:31,115 --> 00:16:32,616
- Oppa, get in the front.
- Thank you.

390
00:16:32,700 --> 00:16:34,618
Okay, keep up the good work.

391
00:16:34,702 --> 00:16:37,162
- Goodbye. Thank you.
- Woo-seok! We're heading out.

392
00:16:37,246 --> 00:16:38,539
- Oh, you're leaving?
- Yeah.

393
00:16:38,622 --> 00:16:40,958
Woo-seok!
Aren't you going to come see us off?

394
00:16:41,667 --> 00:16:43,460
- There's an empty seat.
- Not Woo-seok, Jae-seok.

395
00:16:43,544 --> 00:16:45,087
- There's an empty seat here.
- Aren't I enough?

396
00:16:45,170 --> 00:16:47,423
Woo-seok, we've got an empty seat for you.

397
00:16:47,506 --> 00:16:49,008
- Should I come?
- Yeah, sure.

398
00:16:49,091 --> 00:16:51,552
- Kwang-soo took it.
- Oh, geez. What are you…

399
00:16:51,635 --> 00:16:53,846
- Clean up while I'm gone.
- Kwang-soo, it's okay.

400
00:16:53,929 --> 00:16:55,764
- I just feel bad.
- Seriously. Buckle up.

401
00:16:55,848 --> 00:16:57,683
- Drive safe. I'll see you soon.
- Until next time.

402
00:16:57,766 --> 00:16:59,601
- Is he really going with them?
- Yeah, start cleaning!

403
00:16:59,685 --> 00:17:01,061
Goodbye.

404
00:17:01,145 --> 00:17:03,022
- I feel sad.
- I know.

405
00:17:04,273 --> 00:17:06,984
Kwang-soo, we should just leave.

406
00:17:07,067 --> 00:17:09,653
- This is Woo-seok's B&B anyway.
- Not a bad idea.

407
00:17:10,279 --> 00:17:13,073
- I don't think they'd mind.
- Even if Kwang-soo and I weren't around.

408
00:17:13,157 --> 00:17:15,659
They might even like it.
The vibe might actually get better.

409
00:17:15,743 --> 00:17:18,454
Nothing beats being handsome.
It's annoying, but what can you do?

410
00:17:18,537 --> 00:17:20,956
- There's nothing you can do about it.
- Hilarious.

411
00:17:21,040 --> 00:17:23,167
Ugh, I do really hate to see you go.

412
00:17:23,250 --> 00:17:24,960
- Good time to leave, then.
- For real, seriously.

413
00:17:25,044 --> 00:17:27,546
- Thanks for everything.
- Bye. Bye!

414
00:17:28,464 --> 00:17:30,507
- Bye. See you, hyung.
- Get home safe.

415
00:17:32,634 --> 00:17:34,970
Ugh. To make things easier for me,

416
00:17:35,054 --> 00:17:38,265
Hyo-ri was, you know,
intentionally more involved.

417
00:17:40,017 --> 00:17:43,020
She was constantly stepping in,
more than she had to.

418
00:17:43,103 --> 00:17:45,814
And I was really grateful for that. Yeah.

419
00:17:45,898 --> 00:17:47,399
TEARY-EYED

420
00:17:47,483 --> 00:17:50,402
I hope that they're able to make
a good dinner.

421
00:17:50,486 --> 00:17:52,404
- I'm sure they'll manage it.
- I'm sure.

422
00:17:52,488 --> 00:17:53,989
- Good job.
- Yeah.

423
00:17:55,282 --> 00:17:57,284
Kwang-soo, should we draw our manitos now?

424
00:17:57,367 --> 00:17:58,368
Good idea.

425
00:17:58,452 --> 00:17:59,745
MANITO ALL OF A SUDDEN?

426
00:17:59,828 --> 00:18:03,624
I thought we should do something
different for the second group of guests.

427
00:18:03,707 --> 00:18:07,211
So I said, "Why don't we bring back
the good old manito?"

428
00:18:07,878 --> 00:18:10,255
A GAME OF MANITO
FOR GUEST GROUP 2

429
00:18:11,507 --> 00:18:13,926
Once you're assigned as someone's manito,

430
00:18:14,009 --> 00:18:16,220
you quietly look after them today
without them knowing.

431
00:18:16,303 --> 00:18:17,888
- But don't make it obvious.
- Okay.

432
00:18:18,806 --> 00:18:20,724
- Keep it to yourself.
- Yeah.

433
00:18:21,350 --> 00:18:24,394
EVERYONE QUIETLY CHECKS
THEIR NAME

434
00:18:24,478 --> 00:18:26,772
We're still exchanging gifts randomly,
right?

435
00:18:26,855 --> 00:18:29,358
Do we give our gift
to the person we picked too?

436
00:18:29,441 --> 00:18:31,693
THE STAFF HAS FINISHED
DRAWING TOO

437
00:18:31,777 --> 00:18:34,029
I knew you were all weight lifters.

438
00:18:34,113 --> 00:18:36,573
Bryan keeps talking to me out of nowhere.

439
00:18:36,657 --> 00:18:38,117
- It's like, "There he is."
- Seriously?

440
00:18:38,200 --> 00:18:39,952
He must've picked one of us.

441
00:18:40,035 --> 00:18:42,204
- He's hovering around us.
- You're not fooling us.

442
00:18:42,287 --> 00:18:43,997
So you're already guessing?

443
00:18:44,081 --> 00:18:46,542
All right, guys. Don't tell anyone.

444
00:18:47,334 --> 00:18:49,628
All right,
you can head out to the farm now.

445
00:18:49,711 --> 00:18:51,338
- Let's go!
- Apples!

446
00:18:51,964 --> 00:18:54,842
On the farm, the guests
will have the chance to choose

447
00:18:54,925 --> 00:18:57,261
whichever program they would like
and give it a try.

448
00:18:57,845 --> 00:18:59,805
ENJOY FRESH TANGERINES

449
00:19:00,514 --> 00:19:02,558
AND SWEET APPLES

450
00:19:03,142 --> 00:19:05,978
A SPECIAL OUTDOOR ACTIVITY
AT JAE-SEOK'S B&B

451
00:19:06,061 --> 00:19:08,730
And these are aprons.
Please take one each.

452
00:19:08,814 --> 00:19:11,358
- Everyone, grab one.
- Pass them along.

453
00:19:11,441 --> 00:19:14,361
- Have fun. See you later.
- See you later.

454
00:19:14,444 --> 00:19:15,529
Let's go!

455
00:19:15,612 --> 00:19:17,573
Have fun, everyone. Enjoy.

456
00:19:17,656 --> 00:19:18,824
See you later!

457
00:19:18,907 --> 00:19:20,826
It's like we're leaving for good.

458
00:19:21,451 --> 00:19:24,329
It'll be sad when they leave
like this for real tomorrow.

459
00:19:24,413 --> 00:19:25,581
I know.

460
00:19:26,415 --> 00:19:28,500
- Hey, you okay?
- What?

461
00:19:28,584 --> 00:19:31,253
- No, I thought you were crying.
- Me?

462
00:19:31,336 --> 00:19:33,172
About them leaving.

463
00:19:33,255 --> 00:19:35,465
See you guys later! Let's get it.

464
00:19:35,549 --> 00:19:36,800
Let's go!

465
00:19:36,884 --> 00:19:38,510
Here we go.

466
00:19:38,594 --> 00:19:40,012
We get a little escape.

467
00:19:40,095 --> 00:19:42,097
I've never picked apples before.

468
00:19:42,181 --> 00:19:43,932
Let's pick those trees clean.

469
00:19:44,016 --> 00:19:46,476
Apple picking is fun.

470
00:19:46,560 --> 00:19:48,687
- Let's see who picks best.
- You're on!

471
00:19:48,770 --> 00:19:51,231
- Let's pick the big ones. Look at that.
- There's a pretty one!

472
00:19:51,315 --> 00:19:52,900
- Here we go.
- Careful.

473
00:19:54,318 --> 00:19:56,403
- Now, that's a good dad.
- I got it.

474
00:19:56,486 --> 00:19:59,740
- It's so red and pretty. Look!
- The color is amazing.

475
00:19:59,823 --> 00:20:01,992
That's it. You've almost got it!

476
00:20:02,826 --> 00:20:04,036
The best ones are at the top.

477
00:20:04,119 --> 00:20:05,537
- Oh, thank you!
- Sure.

478
00:20:05,621 --> 00:20:07,956
- Wow, he gave me an apple.
- Ooh!

479
00:20:08,040 --> 00:20:10,834
He gave you an apple?
What's that supposed to mean?

480
00:20:10,918 --> 00:20:12,628
Is he her manito?

481
00:20:12,711 --> 00:20:14,463
He must be her manito!

482
00:20:14,546 --> 00:20:16,340
No, I'm not. I'm 100% sure.

483
00:20:16,423 --> 00:20:18,133
- Busted.
- Busted.

484
00:20:18,217 --> 00:20:19,885
- Or he's flirting with her.
- We'll find out later.

485
00:20:19,968 --> 00:20:20,969
Oh, Mr. Park!

486
00:20:21,053 --> 00:20:23,805
Everyone's busy looking
for the prettiest apple.

487
00:20:23,889 --> 00:20:25,474
Here's a big, red one.

488
00:20:25,557 --> 00:20:27,643
- Wow, we've picked a lot.
- We've got a ton!

489
00:20:27,726 --> 00:20:30,103
I think we've got enough.

490
00:20:30,187 --> 00:20:32,689
The bike rental shop
is only ten minutes away.

491
00:20:32,773 --> 00:20:36,193
Come on! Let's go!

492
00:20:36,276 --> 00:20:37,861
One, two! One, two! One, two!

493
00:20:39,613 --> 00:20:42,407
Oh man, this is great! Let's go!

494
00:20:42,491 --> 00:20:44,993
Now, this is relaxing.

495
00:20:45,744 --> 00:20:47,746
Taste it. It's so sweet.

496
00:20:47,829 --> 00:20:49,706
It's insane.

497
00:20:52,542 --> 00:20:54,002
Good, right?

498
00:20:54,086 --> 00:20:55,796
Wow, it's so sweet.

499
00:20:58,298 --> 00:20:59,341
I got a lot!

500
00:20:59,424 --> 00:21:00,676
This one's cute.

501
00:21:00,759 --> 00:21:02,803
These are the good ones. The small ones.

502
00:21:02,886 --> 00:21:05,013
You know,
I don't think I'm very good at this.

503
00:21:05,097 --> 00:21:07,391
I think we picked
enough to last us a year.

504
00:21:07,474 --> 00:21:09,810
Yeah, I know.
Why do I keep licking my lips?

505
00:21:09,893 --> 00:21:11,144
Well, it is tasty.

506
00:21:11,228 --> 00:21:13,647
This one's for Woo-seok.
Nobody touch it, okay?

507
00:21:14,439 --> 00:21:15,857
It's green.

508
00:21:17,401 --> 00:21:19,111
WOO-SEOK'S TANGERINE

509
00:21:19,194 --> 00:21:21,989
- Hey, that's mine. Why would you take it?
- How did you know?

510
00:21:22,072 --> 00:21:23,865
I'm gonna take you home in a bag.

511
00:21:23,949 --> 00:21:26,159
YIKES

512
00:21:26,243 --> 00:21:28,203
THE NATIONAL TEAM ATHLETE'S
TERRIFYING JOKE

513
00:21:29,538 --> 00:21:31,373
I lay awake at night
'cause I'm scared of her.

514
00:21:31,456 --> 00:21:32,708
Stop lying!

515
00:21:33,333 --> 00:21:35,460
MEANWHILE, JAE-SEOK'S B&B
IS BEING CLEANED

516
00:21:35,544 --> 00:21:37,879
START WITH THE VACUUM

517
00:21:37,963 --> 00:21:40,549
ONCE YOU GET
EVERY NOOK AND CRANNY

518
00:21:41,133 --> 00:21:43,010
THEN IT'S TIME TO MOP

519
00:21:43,635 --> 00:21:45,887
MOP EVERY NOOK AND CRANNY

520
00:21:46,471 --> 00:21:48,724
SCRUB IT CLEAN AND MAKE IT SHINE

521
00:21:48,807 --> 00:21:49,933
You know,

522
00:21:51,059 --> 00:21:53,061
- I'm sleepy.
- Huh?

523
00:21:53,145 --> 00:21:54,938
- I'm tired right now.
- Me too, same.

524
00:21:55,022 --> 00:21:56,148
CHUCKLE

525
00:21:56,231 --> 00:21:58,150
LAUGHING IN DISBELIEF

526
00:21:58,233 --> 00:22:00,986
CURRENT TIME

527
00:22:01,069 --> 00:22:03,613
NO BREAKS
SINCE THEY WOKE UP AT 7 A.M.

528
00:22:03,697 --> 00:22:06,616
I guess you do start to zone out
a bit around this time.

529
00:22:06,700 --> 00:22:08,243
Wow, it's clean.

530
00:22:11,204 --> 00:22:13,457
Ah, such great memories.

531
00:22:13,540 --> 00:22:16,543
- I'll remember this for a long time.
- I know. Me too.

532
00:22:16,626 --> 00:22:19,296
I'll remember the second group
for a long time too.

533
00:22:19,379 --> 00:22:22,132
- Hey, let's take a picture too. Just us.
- Yeah, we should.

534
00:22:22,215 --> 00:22:24,384
- We haven't taken one together.
- I didn't even think of that.

535
00:22:25,010 --> 00:22:27,179
One, two, three.

536
00:22:27,262 --> 00:22:31,183
- Ye-eun, did you wash your hair today?
- I didn't.

537
00:22:31,266 --> 00:22:33,810
- I didn't wanna say anything, but…
- I didn't wash it.

538
00:22:33,894 --> 00:22:35,103
God.

539
00:22:36,688 --> 00:22:38,023
- You're ridiculous.
- I mean…

540
00:22:38,106 --> 00:22:39,107
So funny.

541
00:22:39,191 --> 00:22:40,525
Wow.

542
00:22:40,609 --> 00:22:42,527
- Oh, come on.
- It's really…

543
00:22:42,611 --> 00:22:44,321
It's showing up. Nice.

544
00:22:44,404 --> 00:22:46,615
- I think it came out good.
- Look, we're all in it.

545
00:22:46,698 --> 00:22:49,076
- Are you sure that it's okay?
- My head!

546
00:22:49,159 --> 00:22:51,995
I just kept smiling since I didn't know
when you were gonna take the shot.

547
00:22:52,079 --> 00:22:54,539
Okay, come here, Woo-seok.
Try taking it from this angle.

548
00:22:55,040 --> 00:22:56,958
ONE MORE TIME

549
00:22:57,042 --> 00:22:58,293
Uh, Ye-eun, it's…

550
00:23:00,170 --> 00:23:01,588
AT A LOSS FOR WORDS

551
00:23:01,671 --> 00:23:04,257
- Do I need perfume?
- No, don't. It's fine. I can handle it.

552
00:23:04,341 --> 00:23:05,801
- Deal with it.
- Two, three.

553
00:23:06,968 --> 00:23:08,595
I was holding my breath.

554
00:23:08,678 --> 00:23:10,305
Same.

555
00:23:10,389 --> 00:23:13,850
- Let's all go have a ramyeon.
- Yeah, we gotta eat, right?

556
00:23:13,934 --> 00:23:15,602
Yeah, let's do that.

557
00:23:17,521 --> 00:23:19,356
- I can't wait.
- Thank you.

558
00:23:19,439 --> 00:23:22,067
- This is gonna be good.
- Yeah, it is.

559
00:23:22,984 --> 00:23:25,987
This must be yours, hyung.
It has more water.

560
00:23:26,071 --> 00:23:28,115
- No, this is mine.
- Water. Look, see?

561
00:23:28,198 --> 00:23:30,200
- Oh. This one's mine.
- No, no.

562
00:23:30,283 --> 00:23:32,077
- What do you think?
- Just let him have it.

563
00:23:32,160 --> 00:23:33,870
- He's younger than you.
- Yeah.

564
00:23:33,954 --> 00:23:34,955
Exactly.

565
00:23:35,038 --> 00:23:36,081
CHEEKY

566
00:23:36,164 --> 00:23:37,916
- Let him have it.
- Also…

567
00:23:39,000 --> 00:23:42,504
Kwang-soo, I think you might
just be starved for attention.

568
00:23:42,587 --> 00:23:44,047
CAUGHT (?)

569
00:23:44,131 --> 00:23:45,340
Hyung.

570
00:23:46,800 --> 00:23:48,427
I'll get revenge on everyone.

571
00:23:49,094 --> 00:23:51,346
I can't believe this is happening again!

572
00:23:52,139 --> 00:23:54,391
I didn't notice at first,
but it's getting…

573
00:23:54,474 --> 00:23:56,643
Sorry. That's just how it is
at Jae-seok's B&B.

574
00:23:59,980 --> 00:24:01,982
(LET'S JUST EAT RAMYEON)

575
00:24:03,358 --> 00:24:05,152
This is good.

576
00:24:06,445 --> 00:24:08,155
WOO-SEOK SCARFING IT DOWN

577
00:24:08,238 --> 00:24:11,491
Ramyeon during the wintertime? Wow.

578
00:24:11,575 --> 00:24:12,701
STRAIGHT TO THE BROTH

579
00:24:12,784 --> 00:24:14,619
There's absolutely nothing that beats it.

580
00:24:20,625 --> 00:24:22,669
A PEACEFUL MOMENT FILLED WITH
NOTHING BUT SLURPING SOUNDS

581
00:24:22,752 --> 00:24:23,879
Wait.

582
00:24:25,088 --> 00:24:26,882
What should the awards be this time?

583
00:24:29,009 --> 00:24:30,886
Right, what should we name them this time?

584
00:24:31,761 --> 00:24:33,805
For Seung-jun, how's this?

585
00:24:33,889 --> 00:24:35,932
"Don't Worry.
You Will Dominate the World" award.

586
00:24:36,016 --> 00:24:37,184
That suits him.

587
00:24:38,185 --> 00:24:40,979
For Kwang-chul, I think maybe
the "Best Dad" award.

588
00:24:41,062 --> 00:24:43,148
- He deserves one.
- Honestly, he really is the best dad.

589
00:24:43,231 --> 00:24:45,233
Because in front of his daughters,
it would be…

590
00:24:45,317 --> 00:24:47,444
- Exactly.
- "Thank You for Protecting Us" award?

591
00:24:47,527 --> 00:24:49,446
NOD

592
00:24:49,988 --> 00:24:52,616
OUT OF IDEAS

593
00:24:53,158 --> 00:24:55,202
BACK TO RAMYEON

594
00:24:55,285 --> 00:24:57,120
What time do you think
we should we have dinner?

595
00:24:57,204 --> 00:24:59,039
- Did you say 5:00?
- Around 5:00?

596
00:24:59,122 --> 00:25:02,042
Hey, for the eel later, if you like it
with sauce, we can do that,

597
00:25:02,125 --> 00:25:03,752
but if not, we'll grill it plain.

598
00:25:03,835 --> 00:25:06,296
We could do a combo like last time.

599
00:25:06,379 --> 00:25:09,174
Well, tomorrow's the last night, right?

600
00:25:09,257 --> 00:25:12,344
So instead of just meat,
I got some eel ready.

601
00:25:12,427 --> 00:25:15,555
- Wow!
- I think grilled eel will be incredible.

602
00:25:15,639 --> 00:25:19,059
Looking back at the meals
from the first group, I kept thinking,

603
00:25:19,142 --> 00:25:22,229
"It'd be nice to have something
even better this time."

604
00:25:22,312 --> 00:25:25,273
I wanted to cook them something
really special.

605
00:25:25,357 --> 00:25:27,901
Something that was unique enough
to win them over.

606
00:25:27,984 --> 00:25:31,071
That's when I thought of eel,
like eel rice bowls.

607
00:25:31,154 --> 00:25:33,490
So grill eel on one side
and meat on the other.

608
00:25:33,573 --> 00:25:34,699
Yeah. It was so good.

609
00:25:34,783 --> 00:25:37,869
And when we served the gomtang
in the morning, they really loved it.

610
00:25:37,953 --> 00:25:40,038
- Yeah, the broth.
- I'll try to find that place.

611
00:25:40,121 --> 00:25:41,665
- Let's just pick it up from there.
- Mm-hmm.

612
00:25:41,748 --> 00:25:44,501
We'll leave our pot there
and pick it up in the morning.

613
00:25:44,584 --> 00:25:46,086
So we'll do the barbecue…

614
00:25:46,169 --> 00:25:47,879
- And then the talent show.
- …then the talent show.

615
00:25:47,963 --> 00:25:49,005
Yeah.

616
00:25:49,089 --> 00:25:51,216
All right, then, let's go brush our teeth.

617
00:25:51,299 --> 00:25:53,385
- In a bit.
- We'll go after a short break.

618
00:25:53,468 --> 00:25:54,886
- Sounds good.
- Okay.

619
00:25:54,970 --> 00:25:57,305
- Should we rock-paper-scissors for it?
- Oh, shall we?

620
00:25:57,389 --> 00:25:59,558
- Yeah. There's not that much.
- Right, it's not.

621
00:25:59,641 --> 00:26:01,268
- Rock, paper--
- Hold up.

622
00:26:01,351 --> 00:26:02,435
Wait, hold on.

623
00:26:02,519 --> 00:26:04,563
- You almost won just now.
- Yeah, I know.

624
00:26:04,646 --> 00:26:05,814
All right.

625
00:26:06,606 --> 00:26:08,525
Rock… Rock…

626
00:26:08,608 --> 00:26:09,818
Rock…

627
00:26:09,901 --> 00:26:11,111
Rock, paper, scissors, shoot!

628
00:26:11,194 --> 00:26:13,154
SCISSORS, SCISSORS,
SCISSORS, ROCK

629
00:26:13,238 --> 00:26:14,739
Wow!

630
00:26:14,823 --> 00:26:16,533
I can't help it.

631
00:26:17,284 --> 00:26:18,910
Wow, that's funny.

632
00:26:18,994 --> 00:26:20,120
Interesting.

633
00:26:20,870 --> 00:26:21,997
You won.

634
00:26:23,081 --> 00:26:24,541
WHO WON'T GET TO REST?

635
00:26:24,624 --> 00:26:26,251
Rock, paper, scissors, shoot!

636
00:26:26,334 --> 00:26:27,794
PAPER, ROCK, PAPER

637
00:26:27,877 --> 00:26:28,920
All right!

638
00:26:30,422 --> 00:26:32,757
STUCK WITH CLEANUP & DISHES

639
00:26:32,841 --> 00:26:36,219
Sunbae, this really has been a lot of fun.

640
00:26:36,761 --> 00:26:39,514
I'll clean this up, but shouldn't we pick
someone else for the dishes?

641
00:26:39,598 --> 00:26:41,683
Come on.

642
00:26:41,766 --> 00:26:43,768
What are you talking about?

643
00:26:46,104 --> 00:26:48,940
- You just walk away without looking back.
- Okay.

644
00:26:49,024 --> 00:26:51,610
That's the rule, right? No looking back.

645
00:26:52,444 --> 00:26:53,737
There's no hot water.

646
00:26:54,279 --> 00:26:56,156
Geez, don't talk to me!

647
00:26:57,574 --> 00:26:59,868
- Hyung, thank you.
- Go get some rest.

648
00:26:59,951 --> 00:27:01,911
I'm so happy right now.

649
00:27:01,995 --> 00:27:03,788
Man, this is infuriating.

650
00:27:04,664 --> 00:27:07,000
STARTS DOING THE DISHES
ALL ALONE

651
00:27:07,709 --> 00:27:09,544
I should've picked scissors!

652
00:27:09,628 --> 00:27:10,629
Geez.

653
00:27:11,921 --> 00:27:13,340
Ugh!

654
00:27:13,423 --> 00:27:15,342
THE MORE HE THINKS ABOUT IT,
THE ANGRIER HE GETS

655
00:27:15,425 --> 00:27:16,426
Ugh.

656
00:27:18,595 --> 00:27:20,639
JUST THEN, KWANG-SOO
HEADS TO THE KITCHEN

657
00:27:20,722 --> 00:27:22,766
You little jerk,
showing up when I'm already done?

658
00:27:22,849 --> 00:27:25,018
You little jerk, showing up
when I'm already done?

659
00:27:26,478 --> 00:27:28,772
- Hey! I'm already done!
- No, I didn't know.

660
00:27:28,855 --> 00:27:30,482
- I came to see if you needed help.
- Get out!

661
00:27:30,565 --> 00:27:31,775
- No, listen.
- Go! Go!

662
00:27:31,858 --> 00:27:33,777
If you wanna brush your teeth,
you'd better go now.

663
00:27:33,860 --> 00:27:36,363
KWANG-SOO OFFERS TO FINISH UP

664
00:27:36,446 --> 00:27:38,239
Don't touch what I already did!

665
00:27:38,323 --> 00:27:39,324
HE'S STILL MAD

666
00:27:40,617 --> 00:27:42,494
Woo-seok, it's all done.

667
00:27:43,328 --> 00:27:44,329
Kwang-soo.

668
00:27:45,163 --> 00:27:47,374
Don't worry. I've done it all.

669
00:27:47,457 --> 00:27:49,000
We should head out.

670
00:27:53,838 --> 00:27:57,384
I'm so exhausted
that I'm starting to feel dizzy.

671
00:27:57,467 --> 00:27:59,302
You've got circles under your eyes.

672
00:28:02,430 --> 00:28:05,183
THEY LOAD THE POT

673
00:28:05,266 --> 00:28:06,643
So where to first?

674
00:28:06,726 --> 00:28:08,436
Should we head to the supermarket?

675
00:28:08,520 --> 00:28:09,938
AND HEAD TO
THE SUPERMARKET FIRST

676
00:28:14,359 --> 00:28:15,985
CLATTER

677
00:28:18,321 --> 00:28:20,907
THE CLATTERING IS
THE ONLY SOUND IN THE CAR

678
00:28:25,787 --> 00:28:27,080
FIGHTING OFF SLEEP

679
00:28:27,163 --> 00:28:30,625
(DESPERATELY TRYING
TO STAY AWAKE TOO)

680
00:28:30,709 --> 00:28:32,544
(I CAN'T HELP IT)

681
00:28:34,295 --> 00:28:37,132
HOLDING BACK A YAWN

682
00:28:37,215 --> 00:28:40,093
I guess we were all in need of a break.

683
00:28:44,222 --> 00:28:45,473
Everyone's quiet.

684
00:28:46,433 --> 00:28:47,642
A moment.

685
00:28:48,977 --> 00:28:49,978
At home…

686
00:28:51,813 --> 00:28:53,398
this is how we usually are.

687
00:28:54,941 --> 00:28:56,109
- Right.
- Yeah.

688
00:28:57,569 --> 00:28:58,653
THEY ARRIVE AT THE SUPERMARKET

689
00:28:58,737 --> 00:29:00,238
We don't have to get much, right?

690
00:29:00,321 --> 00:29:01,406
Right.

691
00:29:01,489 --> 00:29:02,907
Hello.

692
00:29:02,991 --> 00:29:04,242
Four of these.

693
00:29:04,325 --> 00:29:07,454
Get plenty of pork belly.
I think people will eat a lot of it. Done.

694
00:29:08,121 --> 00:29:09,831
AFTER A QUICK GROCERY RUN

695
00:29:09,914 --> 00:29:11,916
THEY RUSH OFF AGAIN

696
00:29:12,000 --> 00:29:14,377
We'll come back at 7:30. Yes, thank you.

697
00:29:14,461 --> 00:29:16,421
THINGS TO DO:
DROP OFF THE GOMTANG POT

698
00:29:17,005 --> 00:29:19,090
AND HEAD STRAIGHT BACK TO
THE B&B WITHOUT A MOMENT TO REST

699
00:29:19,174 --> 00:29:20,383
We have to prep.

700
00:29:20,467 --> 00:29:22,510
This whole system is ridiculous.

701
00:29:22,594 --> 00:29:25,889
CURRENT TIME
16:00

702
00:29:27,223 --> 00:29:29,726
THINGS TO DO BEFORE THE GUESTS
RETURN: BARBECUE PREP

703
00:29:29,809 --> 00:29:30,977
Oh, man.

704
00:29:31,060 --> 00:29:32,729
We're doing everything, huh?

705
00:29:32,812 --> 00:29:35,273
It feels like we're running
away from someone.

706
00:29:36,483 --> 00:29:38,234
We're rushing like crazy.

707
00:29:38,943 --> 00:29:41,112
- You know, that's why…
- Yeah?

708
00:29:41,196 --> 00:29:43,490
…my family can't stand
seeing me like this.

709
00:29:43,573 --> 00:29:45,575
Because you don't do this at home?

710
00:29:45,658 --> 00:29:47,702
Yeah, because I never do this at home.

711
00:29:53,082 --> 00:29:54,834
I think this will be easier today.

712
00:29:55,502 --> 00:29:56,669
- You do?
- Yeah.

713
00:29:57,629 --> 00:29:58,922
IGNITES WITHOUT HESITATION

714
00:29:59,005 --> 00:30:01,257
Having done it once
makes a difference, right?

715
00:30:01,341 --> 00:30:04,010
I think it'll catch faster than we expect.

716
00:30:04,093 --> 00:30:06,137
It should get going pretty quickly.

717
00:30:07,347 --> 00:30:10,058
30 MINUTES
INTO LIGHTING THE FIRE

718
00:30:11,935 --> 00:30:12,936
Oh.

719
00:30:13,895 --> 00:30:15,146
SPACING OUT

720
00:30:18,441 --> 00:30:20,193
Isn't this basically fire-gazing?

721
00:30:20,276 --> 00:30:23,321
But fire-gazing isn't stressful.

722
00:30:25,073 --> 00:30:26,157
Right.

723
00:30:27,242 --> 00:30:29,202
MEANWHILE, YE-EUN…

724
00:30:29,869 --> 00:30:32,330
PUTS THE RICE ON

725
00:30:32,413 --> 00:30:34,374
WASHES THE LETTUCE

726
00:30:34,457 --> 00:30:36,501
DOES THE DISHES

727
00:30:36,584 --> 00:30:39,128
SHE'S BUSY SETTING UP
IN THE KITCHEN

728
00:30:40,129 --> 00:30:41,548
I smell barbecue.

729
00:30:41,631 --> 00:30:43,675
Is the fire going?
I think they're working on it.

730
00:30:43,758 --> 00:30:45,385
- Wait, are they grilling something?
- Oh, welcome back!

731
00:30:45,468 --> 00:30:47,428
- Hello!
- Whoa!

732
00:30:47,512 --> 00:30:50,014
- Did you have a good time?
- We got tangerines!

733
00:30:50,098 --> 00:30:52,642
- Wow, you picked a lot!
- Wow.

734
00:30:52,725 --> 00:30:54,769
These are for you, Woo-seok.

735
00:30:55,812 --> 00:30:57,689
- These two.
- Wow, they look delicious!

736
00:30:57,772 --> 00:31:00,358
- They're the prettiest ones. Yeah.
- Thank you so much.

737
00:31:00,441 --> 00:31:02,777
SPECIALLY HANDPICKED BIG,
BEAUTIFUL TANGERINES

738
00:31:02,861 --> 00:31:04,904
Wow, they look delicious.

739
00:31:04,988 --> 00:31:06,406
We left the leaves on.

740
00:31:06,489 --> 00:31:08,116
They say smaller, the better.

741
00:31:08,992 --> 00:31:10,159
Smaller?

742
00:31:10,243 --> 00:31:12,620
Want me to peel one for you
so you can try it?

743
00:31:12,704 --> 00:31:14,038
But isn't this too small?

744
00:31:14,122 --> 00:31:15,874
- No, the smaller ones taste better.
- Oh, really?

745
00:31:16,374 --> 00:31:19,335
NOM NOM

746
00:31:20,169 --> 00:31:21,754
- Mmm!
- It's good, right?

747
00:31:21,838 --> 00:31:23,047
It's good. It's so good.

748
00:31:23,131 --> 00:31:25,884
- Wow! Barbecue time!
- Wow, barbecue!

749
00:31:25,967 --> 00:31:29,470
- Are the apples good?
- Yes! They're really good!

750
00:31:29,554 --> 00:31:31,055
- Take a little break.
- Okay.

751
00:31:31,139 --> 00:31:32,724
TAKE A LITTLE BREAK
WHILE WE GRILL THE MEAT

752
00:31:32,807 --> 00:31:35,059
I think it's pretty much started now.

753
00:31:35,852 --> 00:31:37,645
- Yeah, it's really going.
- So it is.

754
00:31:37,729 --> 00:31:39,230
I'm actually pretty good at this.

755
00:31:39,314 --> 00:31:40,607
HE PUTS THE GRILL ON

756
00:31:40,690 --> 00:31:43,276
CHECKS THE TEMPERATURE
LIKE A PRO

757
00:31:43,985 --> 00:31:45,820
JAE-SEOK'S IN CHARGE
OF THE PORK BELLY

758
00:31:45,904 --> 00:31:47,947
- Looks good, right?
- Yeah.

759
00:31:48,031 --> 00:31:51,659
- And we've also got eel.
- What? Oh.

760
00:31:51,743 --> 00:31:53,202
- I'll grill the eel, hyung.
- Okay.

761
00:31:53,286 --> 00:31:55,747
Bryan, can you bring me the eel
from inside?

762
00:31:55,830 --> 00:31:57,165
Okay.

763
00:31:57,248 --> 00:31:58,791
Here we go.

764
00:31:58,875 --> 00:32:01,085
PRE-ORDERED EEL

765
00:32:01,586 --> 00:32:03,129
STARTING TO GRILL THE EEL TOO

766
00:32:04,130 --> 00:32:05,590
I really hope they like it.

767
00:32:05,673 --> 00:32:08,176
Yeah, I really
wanna make it good for them.

768
00:32:08,927 --> 00:32:11,930
I wonder if the eel was
a good choice or a bad choice.

769
00:32:12,013 --> 00:32:13,973
We should salt it now, right?

770
00:32:14,057 --> 00:32:15,725
But it looks so good!

771
00:32:16,476 --> 00:32:18,061
PORK BELLY IS GOING STRONG

772
00:32:18,144 --> 00:32:20,396
BUT IT'S SLOW
WITH JUST ONE PERSON (!)

773
00:32:20,897 --> 00:32:23,191
STILL A LOT OF PORK BELLY
LEFT TO GRILL

774
00:32:23,274 --> 00:32:25,693
Should I cook some in a frying pan?
To help out?

775
00:32:25,777 --> 00:32:26,778
Go ahead, yeah.

776
00:32:26,861 --> 00:32:29,989
Of course, some people prefer it
charcoal-grilled,

777
00:32:30,073 --> 00:32:33,409
but I used a frying pan
on Kian's Bizarre B&B too.

778
00:32:34,827 --> 00:32:36,329
Need help grilling?

779
00:32:36,412 --> 00:32:39,582
Yeah, if you could just help
with the pork belly in the middle,

780
00:32:39,666 --> 00:32:41,709
- that'd be great, thanks.
- Pork belly here?

781
00:32:41,793 --> 00:32:44,128
- Do we need any salt or pepper?
- Oh, right.

782
00:32:44,212 --> 00:32:45,755
Hey, the seasoning.

783
00:32:46,422 --> 00:32:48,299
You know, the seasoning I brought.

784
00:32:48,383 --> 00:32:51,052
Once you taste this,
you can't go back to regular pork belly.

785
00:32:52,178 --> 00:32:54,097
This'll be way better.

786
00:32:54,180 --> 00:32:55,848
Yeah, now we're prepared.

787
00:32:55,932 --> 00:32:58,184
- We need seasoning for the meat.
- Oh, that's right.

788
00:32:58,267 --> 00:33:00,311
Garlic powder and seasoning.

789
00:33:00,395 --> 00:33:01,896
Should we add the seasoning now?

790
00:33:01,980 --> 00:33:05,274
Yeah, sprinkle it on.
They really loved it last time.

791
00:33:05,358 --> 00:33:08,111
That garlic seasoning's so good.

792
00:33:08,194 --> 00:33:10,154
It even smells different.

793
00:33:10,238 --> 00:33:12,615
Hurry! Come get the meat.
Tell everyone to come.

794
00:33:13,491 --> 00:33:15,952
MAKES A NICE,
HEFTY SSAM RIGHT AWAY

795
00:33:16,035 --> 00:33:18,830
AND TAKES ONE BIG BITE

796
00:33:18,913 --> 00:33:20,832
- It's good. It's really smoky.
- It's so good.

797
00:33:22,500 --> 00:33:23,668
No way. It's so good.

798
00:33:27,046 --> 00:33:28,297
Wow.

799
00:33:28,381 --> 00:33:30,633
Amazing, right? It's really amazing.

800
00:33:30,717 --> 00:33:31,718
Wow.

801
00:33:31,801 --> 00:33:33,636
Whoa, it so good.

802
00:33:33,720 --> 00:33:35,221
Delicious.

803
00:33:35,304 --> 00:33:36,556
That's really good.

804
00:33:36,639 --> 00:33:38,016
It's grilled perfectly.

805
00:33:39,017 --> 00:33:41,811
The eel's taking too long, though.

806
00:33:41,894 --> 00:33:43,855
- Speed is key.
- There's a lot of it.

807
00:33:44,522 --> 00:33:45,565
How's this?

808
00:33:47,900 --> 00:33:49,652
LET'S BORROW SOME PORK BELLY
FROM THE OTHER GRILL

809
00:33:49,736 --> 00:33:52,572
Let's put a few pieces around
and let the fat render.

810
00:33:52,655 --> 00:33:54,574
Oh. Good.

811
00:33:56,784 --> 00:34:00,079
THE FLAMES INTENSIFY QUICKLY

812
00:34:00,163 --> 00:34:02,040
It's starting to cook, right?

813
00:34:02,123 --> 00:34:03,374
Yeah, it's cooking.

814
00:34:04,792 --> 00:34:06,002
Here it comes.

815
00:34:07,378 --> 00:34:10,465
EEL TIME

816
00:34:11,799 --> 00:34:13,634
It looks like it's cooking well.

817
00:34:14,969 --> 00:34:16,387
Jae-seok should try it.

818
00:34:21,309 --> 00:34:22,518
- Oh!
- Is it good?

819
00:34:22,602 --> 00:34:23,603
It's great.

820
00:34:23,686 --> 00:34:26,689
All right.
We just brush it with sauce and serve.

821
00:34:27,774 --> 00:34:29,484
Okay, sauce going on.

822
00:34:31,235 --> 00:34:32,737
This is a total success.

823
00:34:32,820 --> 00:34:34,530
Right? This looks insane.

824
00:34:35,948 --> 00:34:36,949
It's all done.

825
00:34:37,033 --> 00:34:38,409
SERVES THE EEL

826
00:34:38,493 --> 00:34:40,661
- Is this eel?
- Yeah, they made eel too.

827
00:34:40,745 --> 00:34:41,996
Whoa.

828
00:34:42,080 --> 00:34:43,831
MAKES A BIG SSAM

829
00:34:43,915 --> 00:34:44,999
It's eel.

830
00:34:48,086 --> 00:34:50,213
- The eel is insane.
- It's so good.

831
00:34:50,296 --> 00:34:52,673
CHAE-EUN TAKES A BIG BITE TOO

832
00:34:52,757 --> 00:34:53,841
It's good.

833
00:34:54,634 --> 00:34:55,927
Mmm!

834
00:34:56,010 --> 00:34:57,386
- How is it?
- It's insane.

835
00:34:57,470 --> 00:34:58,763
Yeah, it's good?

836
00:34:58,846 --> 00:35:01,933
The meat and the eel are both so good,
don't you think?

837
00:35:02,600 --> 00:35:06,104
Ordering the eel was a brilliant move.
Total game-changer.

838
00:35:06,187 --> 00:35:09,941
It suddenly hit me. I thought,
"It'd be great to serve them some eel."

839
00:35:10,024 --> 00:35:12,318
So you didn't do eel with the first group?

840
00:35:12,401 --> 00:35:14,112
- We just did barbecue.
- Ah.

841
00:35:14,195 --> 00:35:16,197
We'd already had pork belly and all that,

842
00:35:16,280 --> 00:35:18,616
- so eel just felt more…
- You were craving it?

843
00:35:19,242 --> 00:35:21,160
- Good idea.
- Yeah, totally.

844
00:35:21,244 --> 00:35:22,703
Eel was a good call.

845
00:35:22,787 --> 00:35:24,539
- It's incredible.
- Yeah.

846
00:35:24,622 --> 00:35:26,082
Seriously, I think…

847
00:35:27,208 --> 00:35:28,209
the eel was--

848
00:35:28,292 --> 00:35:31,712
SHUT UP AND HAVE SOME EEL

849
00:35:31,796 --> 00:35:33,005
How is it?

850
00:35:33,089 --> 00:35:35,341
- Hye-jeong.
- It's good, right? Oh, boy.

851
00:35:35,424 --> 00:35:37,677
- It's really good, but…
- What's the matter?

852
00:35:37,760 --> 00:35:40,888
- You should've given me a heads-up.
- Oh, I thought you were done.

853
00:35:42,431 --> 00:35:44,308
SSAM DELIVERY SERVICE

854
00:35:44,392 --> 00:35:46,477
- Enjoy.
- Thanks. Oh, that's good.

855
00:35:46,561 --> 00:35:48,104
- For Woo-seok.
- Thanks.

856
00:35:50,940 --> 00:35:51,941
Gosh.

857
00:35:53,234 --> 00:35:54,819
Please enjoy.

858
00:35:54,902 --> 00:35:57,363
AND A FEW POLITE WORDS TOO

859
00:35:59,115 --> 00:36:00,741
My heart almost exploded just now.

860
00:36:00,825 --> 00:36:03,661
Unni, unni, put some meat in here.
It's for Dad.

861
00:36:03,744 --> 00:36:05,454
- Hmm? Is there no more?
- No.

862
00:36:05,538 --> 00:36:08,124
- Do you wanna have some of mine?
- Yes, thanks.

863
00:36:08,666 --> 00:36:09,959
A TOUCH OF SSAMJANG
ON THE PORK BELLY

864
00:36:10,042 --> 00:36:12,753
PLUS EEL

865
00:36:12,837 --> 00:36:15,047
Oh, put some eel in there.

866
00:36:15,131 --> 00:36:16,966
Dad, you gotta try this.

867
00:36:17,633 --> 00:36:19,552
- Let him have it.
- Yeah! Have it.

868
00:36:19,635 --> 00:36:21,345
This might not taste good. Is that okay?

869
00:36:21,429 --> 00:36:23,097
Then give it to your dad.

870
00:36:23,181 --> 00:36:25,349
- Give it to him.
- No, you eat it.

871
00:36:26,309 --> 00:36:28,144
Good. Wow, you know,

872
00:36:28,227 --> 00:36:31,272
an eighth-grader being this sweet,
that's rare.

873
00:36:33,065 --> 00:36:34,734
- I'm really grateful.
- It's rare, I'm telling you.

874
00:36:34,817 --> 00:36:36,485
- You're right.
- It's rare.

875
00:36:37,028 --> 00:36:40,281
WHILE THEY KEEP GRILLING NONSTOP

876
00:36:40,364 --> 00:36:43,075
Ugh. Nothing in this world is easy.

877
00:36:43,576 --> 00:36:45,953
THE GUESTS START COOKING RAMYEON

878
00:36:49,749 --> 00:36:52,460
RAMYEON ON THE SIDE

879
00:36:55,963 --> 00:36:57,965
I didn't even offer this to Woo-seok.

880
00:36:58,049 --> 00:36:59,342
- Really?
- Really.

881
00:36:59,425 --> 00:37:00,676
Wow, thanks.

882
00:37:00,760 --> 00:37:02,261
It's really hot.

883
00:37:02,345 --> 00:37:05,640
TAKING CARE OF THE STAFF
WHO WERE TOO BUSY WORKING TO EAT

884
00:37:07,058 --> 00:37:09,310
- This hits the spot.
- Mmm!

885
00:37:09,393 --> 00:37:11,437
Has anyone gotten you some ramyeon yet?

886
00:37:11,520 --> 00:37:13,481
- Oh, wow.
- Oh, thank you.

887
00:37:13,564 --> 00:37:15,316
- Sure.
- Here. This is for you, Officer.

888
00:37:15,399 --> 00:37:16,567
You're the best, Young-gwang.

889
00:37:24,867 --> 00:37:25,868
Wow.

890
00:37:25,952 --> 00:37:27,578
- Good, right?
- Mmm.

891
00:37:27,662 --> 00:37:30,164
- We haven't added the sauce.
- Should I put it on now?

892
00:37:30,248 --> 00:37:31,958
- I like the sauce.
- Yeah.

893
00:37:32,041 --> 00:37:33,376
I have a kid's palate.

894
00:37:33,459 --> 00:37:36,295
But your health isn't like
a kid's anymore. Careful.

895
00:37:37,046 --> 00:37:39,340
I think your taste buds
are the last thing to age.

896
00:37:39,423 --> 00:37:40,633
- Yeah, you're right.
- Yeah.

897
00:37:41,425 --> 00:37:42,927
- I really love it too.
- Oh, really?

898
00:37:43,010 --> 00:37:44,220
Yeah, I just hold myself back.

899
00:37:44,971 --> 00:37:47,223
I used to be able to eat
a whole cake by myself.

900
00:37:48,057 --> 00:37:50,559
- That's hard to believe.
- I know, right?

901
00:37:50,643 --> 00:37:53,479
But that's life. You have to say
goodbye to the things you love.

902
00:37:53,562 --> 00:37:54,563
I'm gonna cry!

903
00:37:54,647 --> 00:37:57,316
Every time the first digit of your age
changes, you have to give up something.

904
00:37:57,400 --> 00:38:00,695
I think it was about ten years ago
when Jae-seok said,

905
00:38:00,778 --> 00:38:02,863
"I think I should cut back on coffee."

906
00:38:02,947 --> 00:38:04,532
- And he loved coffee.
- Really?

907
00:38:04,615 --> 00:38:05,825
- That's right.
- Oh, really?

908
00:38:05,908 --> 00:38:09,662
And when I hit my late 30s,
I decided I had to quit smoking.

909
00:38:09,745 --> 00:38:11,664
- At some point, it hit me.
- You had to stop.

910
00:38:11,747 --> 00:38:15,042
Yeah. I had to say goodbye
to the things I love.

911
00:38:15,126 --> 00:38:16,752
You leave them one by one.

912
00:38:16,836 --> 00:38:19,130
You're right. That's the reality.

913
00:38:19,213 --> 00:38:20,214
Yeah.

914
00:38:20,298 --> 00:38:22,717
It's been almost two and a half hours
since we started.

915
00:38:22,800 --> 00:38:24,635
We've been at it the whole time.

916
00:38:26,387 --> 00:38:28,889
We should start cleaning this up soon.

917
00:38:28,973 --> 00:38:31,851
- Camping's great and all, but this part…
- The cleanup's brutal.

918
00:38:31,934 --> 00:38:34,312
I'd go camping anytime
if someone else cleaned.

919
00:38:34,395 --> 00:38:35,980
- Me too.
- That's the hard part.

920
00:38:37,356 --> 00:38:39,442
All right, we'd better get started.

921
00:38:39,525 --> 00:38:41,235
TIME TO CLEAN UP

922
00:38:41,319 --> 00:38:43,362
- Thank you for your hard work.
- No trouble at all.

923
00:38:43,446 --> 00:38:45,614
- But you didn't even get to eat.
- No, it's okay.

924
00:38:46,866 --> 00:38:48,117
As long as you enjoyed it.

925
00:38:50,578 --> 00:38:51,579
Ah.

926
00:38:54,498 --> 00:38:57,793
AFTER SETTING OUT
THREE CUPS OF ICE

927
00:38:58,336 --> 00:39:01,547
WHAT DID HE GET?

928
00:39:02,340 --> 00:39:05,634
ZERO-SUGAR COKE

929
00:39:06,302 --> 00:39:08,012
AFTER POURING IT OUT EQUALLY

930
00:39:08,095 --> 00:39:09,221
Kwang-soo.

931
00:39:09,764 --> 00:39:10,848
Oh.

932
00:39:10,931 --> 00:39:12,475
- Thanks, hyung.
- Sure.

933
00:39:13,976 --> 00:39:15,978
I'm gonna go give this to Woo-seok.

934
00:39:16,062 --> 00:39:17,480
Woo-seok.

935
00:39:17,563 --> 00:39:19,190
Yeah, hyung.

936
00:39:19,273 --> 00:39:20,441
For you.

937
00:39:20,524 --> 00:39:21,942
A SWEET TREAT FOR THE STAFF

938
00:39:22,026 --> 00:39:24,236
Wow. Thank you. Is this Coke?

939
00:39:24,320 --> 00:39:25,654
- Yeah, it is.
- Ah, nice.

940
00:39:26,489 --> 00:39:29,283
GULPING IT DOWN

941
00:39:45,841 --> 00:39:49,428
HE'S SO EXHAUSTED
HE'S ACTING STRANGE (?)

942
00:39:51,472 --> 00:39:55,434
BACK TO CLEANING

943
00:39:57,103 --> 00:39:58,270
Let's go.

944
00:39:59,021 --> 00:40:01,565
- Thank you for everything.
- You did great work today too.

945
00:40:01,649 --> 00:40:03,401
- Get some rest.
- See you later.

946
00:40:03,484 --> 00:40:04,652
- Okay.
- Okay.

947
00:40:05,611 --> 00:40:07,071
Done.

948
00:40:07,154 --> 00:40:09,156
Attention, everyone.

949
00:40:09,240 --> 00:40:11,575
I hope you're getting some good rest.

950
00:40:11,659 --> 00:40:16,372
We'll be starting
the talent show/cabaret at 7:30.

951
00:40:16,455 --> 00:40:19,583
We'll see you in the gymnasium shortly.
Thank you.

952
00:40:20,376 --> 00:40:23,170
Oh, wait. I've been wearing these pants
for a while. I should change them.

953
00:40:23,254 --> 00:40:25,089
Hyung, are you finally
changing your pants?

954
00:40:25,172 --> 00:40:28,384
Yeah, I should dress up a little for once.
Navy, my favorite color.

955
00:40:29,844 --> 00:40:31,387
I like gray too, but…

956
00:40:32,179 --> 00:40:33,180
Wow.

957
00:40:36,016 --> 00:40:37,435
Navy looks good on me.

958
00:40:38,310 --> 00:40:39,520
How do I look?

959
00:40:40,646 --> 00:40:42,940
- Did you change?
- Yeah, navy looks good on me, right?

960
00:40:43,023 --> 00:40:44,066
I like you in navy.

961
00:40:44,150 --> 00:40:45,151
- You like?
- Yeah.

962
00:40:45,234 --> 00:40:48,237
I like gray sweatpants too,
but these look…

963
00:40:48,320 --> 00:40:49,321
Finally.

964
00:40:49,405 --> 00:40:51,574
I finally changed my pants,
and it feels great.

965
00:40:51,657 --> 00:40:52,908
You could've changed sooner.

966
00:40:52,992 --> 00:40:54,785
It's the last night.
Feels like the finale.

967
00:40:55,369 --> 00:40:57,746
DAY 1, GRAY SWEATPANTS

968
00:40:57,830 --> 00:41:00,916
DAY 2, GRAY SWEATPANTS

969
00:41:01,000 --> 00:41:04,920
DAY 3, GRAY SWEATPANTS
DAY 4, GRAY SWEATPANTS

970
00:41:05,004 --> 00:41:06,255
Here we go!

971
00:41:07,256 --> 00:41:09,967
DAY 5, GRAY SWEATPANTS

972
00:41:10,050 --> 00:41:11,218
Navy looks good on you.

973
00:41:11,302 --> 00:41:13,053
YEAH?

974
00:41:15,556 --> 00:41:17,475
- He's in a much better mood.
- What's with you?

975
00:41:17,558 --> 00:41:19,435
SECOND TWIRL

976
00:41:19,518 --> 00:41:21,061
Nice.

977
00:41:21,645 --> 00:41:24,106
- You're suddenly all better now.
- Yeah, kind of.

978
00:41:24,190 --> 00:41:26,358
The new pants put him
in a much better mood.

979
00:41:26,442 --> 00:41:28,027
He changed his clothes,
and now he's refreshed.

980
00:41:28,110 --> 00:41:30,613
- They recharged him.
- Yeah. I'm in such a good mood now.

981
00:41:30,696 --> 00:41:33,532
All right, everyone.
Please gather around here.

982
00:41:33,616 --> 00:41:35,826
- What? Are we doing it here?
- Whoa!

983
00:41:35,910 --> 00:41:38,078
A bonfire. Cute.

984
00:41:38,162 --> 00:41:41,040
- Ah, isn't this nice?
- Yeah, it's pretty.

985
00:41:41,707 --> 00:41:43,417
Here, grab a candle.

986
00:41:43,501 --> 00:41:44,543
Take one.

987
00:41:44,627 --> 00:41:46,212
- We've got candles.
- How cute.

988
00:41:46,295 --> 00:41:48,756
We did the campfire outside last time,

989
00:41:48,839 --> 00:41:52,343
but after discussing it,
we felts it's too cold out now.

990
00:41:52,426 --> 00:41:56,138
CURRENT TEMPERATURE 7°C BIG
TEMPERATURE SWINGS IN NOVEMBER

991
00:41:56,222 --> 00:41:59,350
Even with heavy coats on,
you might get cold

992
00:41:59,433 --> 00:42:01,435
