- Oh, yeah, okay.

1460
01:06:20,059 --> 01:06:21,352
Well, hello.

1461
01:06:21,978 --> 01:06:23,312
Hi, I'm Lee Kwang-soo.

1462
01:06:23,396 --> 01:06:27,525
This is a bit of a shock that I'm up here,
but I'll do my best with the song.

1463
01:06:27,608 --> 01:06:30,569
Thank you.

1464
01:06:30,653 --> 01:06:32,697
Please sing the one you do best.

1465
01:06:32,780 --> 01:06:34,865
- Maybe "Prologue"…
- Is "Prologue" okay?

1466
01:06:34,949 --> 01:06:37,702
- Okay, yeah. I'll sing "Prologue."
- No way.

1467
01:06:37,785 --> 01:06:39,787
You can't do something
a little more upbeat, can you?

1468
01:06:39,870 --> 01:06:42,248
- More upbeat? Like what?
- Just do "Prologue." It's fine.

1469
01:06:43,958 --> 01:06:46,002
"Like the Strong Salmon"…

1470
01:06:46,085 --> 01:06:49,005
Oh, let's do that!
"Like the Strong Salmon." Yeah.

1471
01:06:50,256 --> 01:06:51,632
Let's go!

1472
01:06:53,384 --> 01:06:56,971
"LIKE THE POWERFUL SALMON
SWIMMING UPSTREAM"

1473
01:06:57,054 --> 01:06:59,432
BY KANG SAN-EH

1474
01:06:59,515 --> 01:07:01,809
Oh, no. Even I'm embarrassed.

1475
01:07:03,019 --> 01:07:05,354
I'M EMBARRASSED TOO…

1476
01:07:06,063 --> 01:07:10,776
<i>Like salmon swimming upstream </i>

1477
01:07:10,860 --> 01:07:13,904
<i>Against the current </i>

1478
01:07:14,572 --> 01:07:17,241
- Oh, he's good.
- He's actually really good.

1479
01:07:17,324 --> 01:07:20,327
<i>For reasons only they seem to know </i>

1480
01:07:20,411 --> 01:07:21,454
<i>Mysterious reasons… </i>

1481
01:07:21,537 --> 01:07:22,580
I'm impressed.

1482
01:07:23,330 --> 01:07:24,582
Oh, my gosh!

1483
01:07:25,374 --> 01:07:27,334
He's actually pretty good.

1484
01:07:27,418 --> 01:07:31,756
<i>For as long as I can remember </i>

1485
01:07:31,839 --> 01:07:35,301
<i>I've been walking</i>
<i>And walking this road </i>

1486
01:07:36,135 --> 01:07:40,264
<i>I wonder how much farther </i>

1487
01:07:40,347 --> 01:07:43,601
<i>I still have to go </i>

1488
01:07:44,435 --> 01:07:47,688
HYPE METER

1489
01:07:47,772 --> 01:07:52,276
<i>Among the many branching paths</i>
<i>Even if this turns out to be </i>

1490
01:07:52,359 --> 01:07:55,488
<i>The one I'm walking on </i>

1491
01:07:56,697 --> 01:08:00,201
<i>A winding road that forces me </i>

1492
01:08:00,284 --> 01:08:06,082
<i>To go the long way around </i>

1493
01:08:07,208 --> 01:08:11,337
<i>The soles of my feet grow hard </i>

1494
01:08:12,379 --> 01:08:15,549
<i>But if I just keep walking and walking </i>

1495
01:08:16,425 --> 01:08:20,179
<i>I'll get to lie down</i>
<i>In that wide field of flowers </i>

1496
01:08:20,262 --> 01:08:23,724
<i>And finally rest </i>

1497
01:08:24,433 --> 01:08:26,477
He's good.

1498
01:08:30,147 --> 01:08:32,441
Okay. Thank you!

1499
01:08:34,860 --> 01:08:36,070
HUH?

1500
01:08:37,822 --> 01:08:40,116
All right. I'm a little disappointed.

1501
01:08:40,199 --> 01:08:41,867
Sorry?

1502
01:08:41,951 --> 01:08:43,577
- You forced me up here.
- I mean…

1503
01:08:43,661 --> 01:08:46,747
I was just starting to get into it, and
then it ended. That's a bit of a shame.

1504
01:08:46,831 --> 01:08:49,708
Okay. Thank you!

1505
01:08:49,792 --> 01:08:51,168
I wanted to dance,

1506
01:08:51,252 --> 01:08:55,256
but "Like the Strong Salmon"
isn't exactly a great song to dance to.

1507
01:08:56,048 --> 01:08:57,591
- Well, thanks anyway.
- Wait, what?

1508
01:08:58,634 --> 01:09:00,052
What are you…

1509
01:09:00,136 --> 01:09:03,472
- Oh, sorry.
- No, you told me to sing a quiet ballad!

1510
01:09:03,556 --> 01:09:06,225
You're a celeb. I had high expectations.

1511
01:09:06,308 --> 01:09:08,018
What's wrong with him?

1512
01:09:10,146 --> 01:09:12,690
You're humiliating me
in front of everyone!

1513
01:09:13,399 --> 01:09:16,110
Now I feel like this whole party
is ruined because of me!

1514
01:09:16,819 --> 01:09:19,071
Your singing was really good, though.

1515
01:09:19,155 --> 01:09:21,782
- What is the matter with him?
- All right, tonight… Yeah.

1516
01:09:21,866 --> 01:09:25,536
Uh, Kwang-soo just did
a fantastic job with "Salmon."

1517
01:09:25,619 --> 01:09:27,872
Now, when we had
our first group of guests,

1518
01:09:27,955 --> 01:09:31,458
Woo-seok sang,
but he wasn't feeling very well.

1519
01:09:31,542 --> 01:09:33,669
So, since you all came this far…

1520
01:09:33,752 --> 01:09:37,047
- Wow, really? He's going to sing?
- Well, it's been a while, but…

1521
01:09:37,131 --> 01:09:41,260
Kwang-soo was so great, how about
we hear Woo-seok sing "Sudden Shower"?

1522
01:09:41,343 --> 01:09:43,345
This is crazy.

1523
01:09:43,429 --> 01:09:45,723
Why would you use me like this?

1524
01:09:45,806 --> 01:09:48,684
- No, I wasn't…
- This was all to make him sing, wasn't it?

1525
01:09:48,767 --> 01:09:51,187
I was going to end it with "Salmon,"

1526
01:09:51,270 --> 01:09:53,647
- but it just felt like… Yeah.
- Wow! No way.

1527
01:09:53,731 --> 01:09:55,941
- This is awesome.
- I can't say no.

1528
01:09:56,025 --> 01:09:57,234
Let's hear it!

1529
01:09:59,069 --> 01:10:00,946
EXCITED

1530
01:10:01,780 --> 01:10:03,699
QUICKLY CLEARING HIS THROAT

1531
01:10:03,782 --> 01:10:05,618
Aw, Sun-jae!

1532
01:10:05,701 --> 01:10:08,204
I can't believe we're hearing this live.

1533
01:10:09,914 --> 01:10:14,793
"SUDDEN SHOWER" BY ECLIPSE

1534
01:10:17,755 --> 01:10:22,718
<i>I hoped it wouldn't stop </i>

1535
01:10:24,470 --> 01:10:28,140
My heart is melting, guys.
My heart is melting.

1536
01:10:30,935 --> 01:10:34,480
<i>I desperately hoped </i>

1537
01:10:34,563 --> 01:10:38,275
<i>It wasn't just a passing rain </i>

1538
01:10:38,359 --> 01:10:42,613
<i>That only lasts for a moment </i>

1539
01:10:43,948 --> 01:10:46,575
<i>Do you know how I feel? </i>

1540
01:10:46,659 --> 01:10:47,785
He's singing to me.

1541
01:10:47,868 --> 01:10:52,414
<i>I've been thinking about you every day </i>

1542
01:10:52,498 --> 01:10:57,544
<i>Each day, you soak into my heart </i>

1543
01:10:58,629 --> 01:11:01,465
<i>You are a gift </i>

1544
01:11:01,548 --> 01:11:03,050
Byeon Woo-seok!

1545
01:11:03,133 --> 01:11:05,344
<i>Sent down from the sky </i>

1546
01:11:05,427 --> 01:11:09,723
<i>In this world where you stand alone </i>

1547
01:11:09,807 --> 01:11:12,184
I wanna run up there and turn it off.

1548
01:11:12,268 --> 01:11:13,852
Byeon Woo-seok!

1549
01:11:13,936 --> 01:11:17,815
<i>You came into my life one day </i>

1550
01:11:17,898 --> 01:11:20,985
<i>Like a sudden shower </i>

1551
01:11:21,068 --> 01:11:24,780
<i>But I carve you into my heart</i>
<i>Once again today </i>

1552
01:11:24,863 --> 01:11:28,617
<i>You, my gift </i>

1553
01:11:29,868 --> 01:11:31,287
<i>My love </i>

1554
01:11:31,370 --> 01:11:32,621
That was insane!

1555
01:11:32,705 --> 01:11:34,039
<i>My love </i>

1556
01:11:34,123 --> 01:11:35,416
That was insane!

1557
01:11:37,418 --> 01:11:41,046
Wow, that was insane! Totally insane!

1558
01:11:42,840 --> 01:11:44,758
I think I'm gonna pass out!

1559
01:11:44,842 --> 01:11:46,760
My heart just stopped.

1560
01:11:46,844 --> 01:11:48,554
- My hands are shaking.
- Let's hear it!

1561
01:11:48,637 --> 01:11:50,431
My heart is done!

1562
01:11:50,514 --> 01:11:54,143
Wow. Let's give Woo-seok
another round of applause.

1563
01:11:54,226 --> 01:11:55,602
HURT ONCE AGAIN…

1564
01:11:55,686 --> 01:11:58,022
- I didn't mean for this to happen…
- My hands are shaking.

1565
01:11:58,105 --> 01:12:00,858
…but Kwang-soo's
in an even worse spot now.

1566
01:12:00,941 --> 01:12:04,820
It's worse than with the first group!
I really didn't mean for this to happen.

1567
01:12:04,903 --> 01:12:07,865
It's okay! It's okay!

1568
01:12:09,742 --> 01:12:12,202
All right. We've heard the Earring Prince…

1569
01:12:12,286 --> 01:12:16,206
All right. We've heard The Earring Prince,
and, uh, the Prince.

1570
01:12:16,290 --> 01:12:18,125
- The two of them…
- "The Earring Prince."

1571
01:12:20,002 --> 01:12:21,628
- Oh, no.
- Right.

1572
01:12:21,712 --> 01:12:25,716
That was the Earring Prince
and the Prince on stage.

1573
01:12:25,799 --> 01:12:28,552
Ye-eun, did you say you want to sing
"Without a Heart" with Kwang-soo?

1574
01:12:28,635 --> 01:12:30,095
- Yeah.
- Wow!

1575
01:12:30,804 --> 01:12:33,098
Me? Why me?

1576
01:12:33,182 --> 01:12:34,683
8eight was a trio, you know.

1577
01:12:34,767 --> 01:12:37,353
- Oh, with Woo-seok too?
- Yes, the three of us.

1578
01:12:37,436 --> 01:12:39,438
- Me too?
- Heck, yeah. That's awesome.

1579
01:12:39,521 --> 01:12:42,066
All right, then.
The Earring Prince, the Prince,

1580
01:12:42,149 --> 01:12:44,276
and Princess Big Appetite,
please come up to the stage.

1581
01:12:44,360 --> 01:12:45,944
Let's hear it! All right.

1582
01:12:46,028 --> 01:12:48,238
READY OR NOT,
THE STAFF TRIO STEPS UP

1583
01:12:48,322 --> 01:12:51,408
This is your chance, Kwang-soo.
This is your chance to make up for it.

1584
01:12:51,492 --> 01:12:53,369
- But I don't… No, not really.
- Do you know this?

1585
01:12:53,452 --> 01:12:54,453
Oh, right.

1586
01:12:54,536 --> 01:12:57,831
All right, let's get the music ready.
Ye-eun, say hi to everyone.

1587
01:12:57,915 --> 01:13:01,043
Hello! We are 8eight!

1588
01:13:01,126 --> 01:13:02,211
That's us.

1589
01:13:05,047 --> 01:13:07,007
I can add harmonies, so please keep it

1590
01:13:07,091 --> 01:13:08,425
in the original key.

1591
01:13:08,509 --> 01:13:09,927
Okay. I like to harmonize.

1592
01:13:10,010 --> 01:13:12,054
We start together.

1593
01:13:12,137 --> 01:13:13,639
I know.

1594
01:13:13,722 --> 01:13:17,184
<i>…say it hurts I feel like it really will</i>

1595
01:13:17,267 --> 01:13:19,186
What happened to singing harmony?

1596
01:13:19,269 --> 01:13:23,065
<i>If I say I'm sad</i>
<i>I feel like I'll start crying </i>

1597
01:13:23,982 --> 01:13:28,946
<i>So I just smile</i>
<i>Just smile, just smile </i>

1598
01:13:29,696 --> 01:13:32,449
<i>But people still ask me why I'm crying </i>

1599
01:13:32,533 --> 01:13:34,034
That's adorable.

1600
01:13:34,660 --> 01:13:36,370
<i>I have no heart </i>

1601
01:13:36,453 --> 01:13:37,538
Together.

1602
01:13:37,621 --> 01:13:40,332
<i>I have no heart </i>

1603
01:13:40,416 --> 01:13:43,877
<i>So I could never feel heartbroken </i>

1604
01:13:46,130 --> 01:13:48,424
<i>Every day I tell myself this </i>

1605
01:13:48,507 --> 01:13:51,176
<i>Like I'm casting a spell </i>

1606
01:13:51,260 --> 01:13:55,305
<i>And still, the tears keep coming </i>

1607
01:13:55,389 --> 01:13:56,473
OUT OF TUNE

1608
01:13:56,557 --> 01:13:59,393
<i>If I say it hurts </i>

1609
01:13:59,476 --> 01:14:02,187
<i>I feel like it really will </i>

1610
01:14:02,271 --> 01:14:04,857
<i>If I say I'm sad </i>

1611
01:14:04,940 --> 01:14:07,651
<i>I feel like I'll start crying </i>

1612
01:14:07,734 --> 01:14:12,072
<i>So I just smile</i>
<i>Just smile, just smile </i>

1613
01:14:14,074 --> 01:14:16,618
It's been so
long since I've done something like this,

1614
01:14:16,702 --> 01:14:17,828
and I really enjoyed it.

1615
01:14:17,911 --> 01:14:20,330
It felt like we were on a school trip,
just having fun together.

1616
01:14:20,414 --> 01:14:23,542
This was a chance for me
to show a different side of myself,

1617
01:14:23,625 --> 01:14:25,461
and it really took me by surprise.

1618
01:14:26,378 --> 01:14:28,839
All those moments
we spent laughing and talking

1619
01:14:28,922 --> 01:14:31,675
made me really, really happy.

1620
01:14:32,885 --> 01:14:35,429
<i>I have no heart </i>

1621
01:14:35,512 --> 01:14:37,264
<i>I have no heart </i>

1622
01:14:38,056 --> 01:14:40,601
<i>I have no heart </i>

1623
01:14:40,684 --> 01:14:42,394
<i>So I can't be heartbroken </i>

1624
01:14:42,478 --> 01:14:43,812
All right.

1625
01:14:43,896 --> 01:14:45,522
- <i>So I just smile…</i>
- All right, so…

1626
01:14:45,606 --> 01:14:49,943
Okay, so, let's give these three
another big round of applause.

1627
01:14:50,027 --> 01:14:52,613
Thank you.

1628
01:14:54,031 --> 01:14:56,200
Oh, gosh. That was crazy.

1629
01:14:56,283 --> 01:14:59,286
Well, led by Ji Ye-eun,
let's hear it for this trio.

1630
01:14:59,369 --> 01:15:01,788
That was a great performance
of "Without a Heart."

1631
01:15:01,872 --> 01:15:05,375
Please, give them all
another big round of applause.

1632
01:15:05,459 --> 01:15:07,753
YE-EUN IS SATISFIED
WITH THE PERFORMANCE

1633
01:15:07,836 --> 01:15:10,172
All right, everyone. Unfortunately,

1634
01:15:10,255 --> 01:15:13,258
it's our last night,
and there isn't much time left.

1635
01:15:13,342 --> 01:15:15,636
JAE-SEOK'S B&B RULES!
